---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="AI & Machine Learning · Virtual Labs · AquinTutor" description="Eight machine-learning experiments that genuinely train live — gradient descent, logistic & linear regression, k-NN, k-means, decision trees, PCA, backprop neural nets and optimizer comparison.">
<style>
  body { background:#0a0a0c; color:#e8e8ee; margin:0; font-family:ui-monospace,'Geist Mono',monospace; }
  .wrap { max-width:1240px; margin:0 auto; padding:40px 24px 96px; }
  .back { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:7px; font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#9aa0aa; text-decoration:none; margin-bottom:26px; }
  .back:hover { color:#67e8f9; }
  .back svg { width:14px; height:14px; }
  .eyebrow { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.18em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#67e8f9; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:12px; }
  h1.title { font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif; font-size:clamp(34px,5vw,52px); font-weight:600; letter-spacing:-0.02em; line-height:1.05; margin:0 0 12px; }
  h1.title em { color:#a78bfa; font-style:italic; font-weight:500; }
  .lede { color:#9aa0aa; max-width:760px; font-size:14px; line-height:1.65; margin-bottom:26px; font-family:ui-monospace,'Geist Mono',monospace; }

  /* shell: experiment sidebar + content */
  .shell { display:grid; grid-template-columns:262px minmax(0,1fr); gap:22px; align-items:start; }
  @media (max-width:980px){ .shell { grid-template-columns:1fr; } }
  .explist { background:#11131a; border:1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius:12px; padding:10px; position:sticky; top:18px; }
  .explist h4 { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.16em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#9aa0aa; font-weight:700; margin:6px 8px 10px; }
  .exitem { display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:10px; width:100%; text-align:left; background:transparent; border:1px solid transparent; color:#cfd6da; padding:9px 10px; border-radius:8px; cursor:pointer; font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:12px; line-height:1.35; margin-bottom:2px; }
  .exitem:hover { background:#0a0a0c; color:#e8e8ee; }
  .exitem.active { background:#67e8f9; color:#04161b; font-weight:700; }
  .exitem .ix { font-size:10px; opacity:0.8; min-width:18px; }
  .exitem.active .ix { opacity:0.9; }

  /* content area */
  .content { min-width:0; }
  .exptitle { font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif; font-size:30px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:-0.01em; margin:0 0 4px; color:#e8e8ee; }
  .expsub { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:11px; color:#9aa0aa; margin:0 0 16px; letter-spacing:0.03em; }

  .tabs { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:6px; margin-bottom:20px; border-bottom:1px solid #2a2a35; padding-bottom:0; }
  .tab { background:transparent; border:1px solid transparent; border-bottom:none; color:#9aa0aa; padding:9px 14px; font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.06em; text-transform:uppercase; cursor:pointer; border-radius:8px 8px 0 0; position:relative; top:1px; }
  .tab:hover { color:#e8e8ee; }
  .tab.active { color:#0a0a0c; background:#67e8f9; font-weight:700; }

  .sect { display:none; }
  .sect.active { display:block; }
  .prose { font-family:ui-monospace,'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:13px; color:#cfd6da; line-height:1.75; max-width:780px; }
  .prose h5 { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.16em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#67e8f9; font-weight:700; margin:0 0 12px; }
  .prose p { margin:0 0 14px; }
  .prose ol, .prose ul { margin:0 0 14px; padding-left:22px; }
  .prose li { margin-bottom:8px; }
  .prose strong { color:#e8e8ee; }
  .eq { background:#11131a; border:1px solid #2a2a35; border-left:3px solid #a78bfa; border-radius:8px; padding:11px 14px; margin:0 0 12px; font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:12.5px; color:#fbbf24; line-height:1.7; overflow-x:auto; }
  .eq .lbl { color:#9aa0aa; }
  .refs { font-family:ui-monospace,'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12px; color:#cfd6da; line-height:1.7; }
  .refs li { margin-bottom:12px; }
  .refs .who { color:#67e8f9; }

  .grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:minmax(0,1fr) 320px; gap:18px; align-items:start; }
  @media (max-width:920px){ .grid { grid-template-columns:1fr; } }
  .panel { background:#11131a; border:1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius:12px; padding:16px; }
  .panel h3 { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.16em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#67e8f9; font-weight:700; margin:0 0 12px; }
  canvas { display:block; width:100%; background:#0a0a0c; border:1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius:10px; cursor:crosshair; }
  canvas.loss { cursor:default; height:150px; margin-top:14px; }
  .row { display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:center; margin-bottom:13px; flex-wrap:wrap; }
  .row > label { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#9aa0aa; min-width:74px; }
  select, input[type=range] { background:#0a0a0c; border:1px solid #2a2a35; color:#fff; padding:7px 10px; border-radius:5px; font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:12px; flex:1; }
  input[type=range] { padding:0; height:24px; accent-color:#a78bfa; }
  .val { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:12px; color:#fbbf24; min-width:54px; text-align:right; }
  .btn { background:#67e8f9; color:#04161b; padding:9px 14px; border:none; border-radius:6px; font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:11px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.05em; text-transform:uppercase; cursor:pointer; }
  .btn:hover { background:#7ff0ff; }
  .btn.purple { background:#a78bfa; color:#0a0a0c; }
  .btn.purple:hover { background:#bda5ff; }
  .btn.ghost { background:transparent; color:#cfd6da; border:1px solid #2a2a35; }
  .btn.ghost:hover { border-color:#67e8f9; color:#67e8f9; }
  .btn:disabled { opacity:0.4; cursor:not-allowed; }
  .btns { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:8px; margin-top:6px; }
  .btns .full { grid-column:1 / -1; }
  .stats { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:8px; margin-top:14px; }
  .stat { background:#0a0a0c; border:1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius:6px; padding:8px 10px; }
  .stat .label { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:9px; letter-spacing:0.13em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#9aa0aa; }
  .stat .value { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:18px; color:#86efac; font-weight:700; margin-top:2px; word-break:break-all; }
  .stat .value.cy { color:#67e8f9; } .stat .value.pu { color:#a78bfa; } .stat .value.am { color:#fbbf24; }
  .helptext { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:10px; color:#9aa0aa; line-height:1.7; margin-top:12px; }
  .helptext code { color:#67e8f9; background:#0a0a0c; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:3px; }
  .helptext strong { color:#e8e8ee; }
  .legend { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; margin-top:12px; font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:10px; color:#cfd6da; }
  .legend > span { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:6px; }
  .dot { width:11px; height:11px; border-radius:50%; display:inline-block; }
  .seg { display:inline-flex; border:1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius:6px; overflow:hidden; }
  .seg button { background:#0a0a0c; color:#9aa0aa; border:none; padding:7px 12px; font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:11px; cursor:pointer; }
  .seg button.on { background:#a78bfa; color:#0a0a0c; font-weight:700; }

  /* self-assessment */
  .quiz { max-width:780px; }
  .q { background:#11131a; border:1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius:10px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:14px; }
  .q .qq { font-family:ui-monospace,'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:13px; color:#e8e8ee; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:10px; }
  .q .opt { display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:9px; padding:7px 9px; border:1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius:7px; margin-bottom:6px; cursor:pointer; font-family:ui-monospace,'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12.5px; color:#cfd6da; }
  .q .opt:hover { border-color:#67e8f9; }
  .q .opt input { accent-color:#67e8f9; margin-top:2px; }
  .q .opt.correct { border-color:#86efac; background:rgba(134,239,172,0.08); color:#bbf7d0; }
  .q .opt.wrong { border-color:#fca5a5; background:rgba(252,165,165,0.08); color:#fecaca; }
  .q .expl { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:11px; color:#9aa0aa; line-height:1.6; margin-top:8px; display:none; }
  .q .expl.show { display:block; }
  .q .expl b { color:#86efac; }
  .quizbar { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px; margin-top:6px; }
  .quizscore { font-family:'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; font-size:13px; color:#fbbf24; font-weight:700; }
</style>
<main class="wrap">
  <a class="back" href="/aquintutor/labs">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M19 12H5M12 19l-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
    All virtual labs
  </a>
  <div class="eyebrow">Lab 15 &middot; Artificial Intelligence</div>
  <h1 class="title">AI &amp; Machine <em>Learning</em></h1>
  <p class="lede">Eight machine-learning experiments that genuinely train in your browser — no precomputed results, no libraries. Every model hand-rolls its own math: gradient descent, backpropagation, Lloyd's algorithm, recursive Gini splits, power-iteration eigenvectors and three named optimizers. Pick an experiment, read the theory, then run the live simulation.</p>

  <div class="shell">
    <!-- ===== EXPERIMENT SIDEBAR ===== -->
    <nav class="explist" id="explist">
      <h4>Experiments</h4>
      <button class="exitem active" data-exp="reg"><span class="ix">01</span><span>Linear regression (gradient descent)</span></button>
      <button class="exitem" data-exp="logit"><span class="ix">02</span><span>Logistic regression</span></button>
      <button class="exitem" data-exp="knn"><span class="ix">03</span><span>k-NN classification regions</span></button>
      <button class="exitem" data-exp="km"><span class="ix">04</span><span>k-means clustering</span></button>
      <button class="exitem" data-exp="tree"><span class="ix">05</span><span>Decision tree classifier</span></button>
      <button class="exitem" data-exp="pca"><span class="ix">06</span><span>PCA dimensionality reduction</span></button>
      <button class="exitem" data-exp="nn"><span class="ix">07</span><span>Neural network (MLP backprop)</span></button>
      <button class="exitem" data-exp="opt"><span class="ix">08</span><span>Optimizers compared</span></button>
    </nav>

    <!-- ===== CONTENT ===== -->
    <div class="content">
      <h2 class="exptitle" id="expTitle">Linear regression via gradient descent</h2>
      <p class="expsub" id="expSub">Experiment 01 &middot; supervised learning &middot; mean-squared-error minimisation</p>

      <div class="tabs" id="tabs">
        <button class="tab active" data-tab="aim">Aim</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="theory">Theory</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="proc">Procedure</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="sim">Simulation</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="quiz">Self-assessment</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="ref">References</button>
      </div>

      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <!-- EXP 1 : LINEAR REGRESSION                              -->
      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <div class="expbody" id="body-reg">
        <div class="sect active" data-sect="aim">
          <div class="prose">
            <h5>Aim</h5>
            <p>To fit a straight line <strong>y = w&middot;x + b</strong> to a set of scattered 2-D points by minimising the mean-squared error using batch gradient descent, and to observe how the learning rate controls convergence of the loss curve.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="theory">
          <div class="prose">
            <h5>Theory</h5>
            <p>Linear regression assumes the target is an affine function of the input plus noise. Training searches for the parameters (w, b) that minimise the mean-squared error (MSE) over all n samples. Because MSE is convex and differentiable, we can descend its gradient: at every step we move the parameters a small amount (the learning rate) in the direction of steepest decrease.</p>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">prediction</span>  y_hat = w&middot;x + b</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">loss (MSE)</span>  L = (1/n) &Sigma; (y_hat_i - y_i)^2</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">gradients</span>  dL/dw = (2/n) &Sigma; (y_hat_i - y_i)&middot;x_i ,  dL/db = (2/n) &Sigma; (y_hat_i - y_i)</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">update</span>  w &larr; w - &eta;&middot;dL/dw ,  b &larr; b - &eta;&middot;dL/db</div>
            <p>The coefficient of determination R&sup2; = 1 - SS_res/SS_tot reports the fraction of variance explained; R&sup2; = 1 is a perfect fit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="proc">
          <div class="prose">
            <h5>Procedure</h5>
            <ol>
              <li>Press <strong>Sample data</strong> to load a noisy linear cloud, or click anywhere on the plot to drop your own (x, y) points.</li>
              <li>Set the <strong>learning rate</strong> with the slider (log scale).</li>
              <li>Press <strong>Train</strong> to run gradient descent continuously, or <strong>Step</strong> to advance a few epochs at a time.</li>
              <li>Watch the purple line rotate into place while the amber MSE curve falls each epoch.</li>
              <li>Read the converged weight, bias and R&sup2;; try a learning rate that is too high to see the loss diverge.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="sim">
          <div class="grid">
            <div class="panel">
              <h3>Gradient descent &middot; MSE loss</h3>
              <canvas id="regCanvas" width="760" height="440"></canvas>
              <canvas id="regLoss" class="loss" width="760" height="150"></canvas>
              <div class="helptext"><strong>Click</strong> the plot to drop <code>(x, y)</code> points. Gradient descent fits <code>y = w&middot;x + b</code> by minimising mean-squared error; the line and loss curve update every epoch.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="panel">
                <h3>Controls</h3>
                <div class="row"><label>Learn rate</label><input type="range" id="regLr" min="-4" max="0" step="0.05" value="-1.3"><span class="val" id="regLrV">0.05</span></div>
                <div class="btns">
                  <button class="btn" id="regRun">Train</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost" id="regStep">Step</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="regSeed">Sample data</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="regClear">Clear points</button>
                </div>
                <div class="stats">
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">weight w</div><div class="value cy" id="regW">0.000</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">bias b</div><div class="value pu" id="regB">0.000</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">MSE loss</div><div class="value" id="regL">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">epoch</div><div class="value am" id="regE">0</div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="panel" style="margin-top:14px;">
                <h3>R&sup2; goodness of fit</h3>
                <div class="stat"><div class="value am" id="regR2" style="font-size:24px;">--</div></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="reg"></div></div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="ref">
          <div class="prose"><h5>References</h5>
            <ul class="refs">
              <li><span class="who">Bishop, C. M.</span> <em>Pattern Recognition and Machine Learning</em>, Springer 2006 — Ch. 3, Linear Models for Regression.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Hastie, Tibshirani &amp; Friedman.</span> <em>The Elements of Statistical Learning</em>, 2nd ed., Springer 2009 — Ch. 3.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Goodfellow, Bengio &amp; Courville.</span> <em>Deep Learning</em>, MIT Press 2016 — Ch. 4-5 on gradient-based optimisation.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <!-- EXP 2 : LOGISTIC REGRESSION (NEW)                      -->
      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <div class="expbody" id="body-logit" style="display:none;">
        <div class="sect active" data-sect="aim">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Aim</h5>
            <p>To train a binary classifier by logistic regression — pushing a linear score through the sigmoid function and minimising binary cross-entropy with gradient descent — and to visualise the learned linear decision boundary.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="theory">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Theory</h5>
            <p>Logistic regression models the probability that a point belongs to class 1 as the sigmoid of a linear score. The sigmoid squashes any real number into (0, 1). We fit the weights by minimising binary cross-entropy (log-loss); a convenient property is that its gradient has the same simple form as linear regression — the error (prediction minus label) times the input.</p>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">score</span>  z = w1&middot;x1 + w2&middot;x2 + b</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">sigmoid</span>  p = &sigma;(z) = 1 / (1 + e^(-z))</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">loss (BCE)</span>  L = -(1/n) &Sigma; [ y&middot;ln(p) + (1-y)&middot;ln(1-p) ]</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">gradient</span>  dL/dw_j = (1/n) &Sigma; (p_i - y_i)&middot;x_ij</div>
            <p>The decision boundary is the line z = 0, i.e. where p = 0.5. It is always straight (linear) for this model.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="proc">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Procedure</h5>
            <ol>
              <li>Choose the active class (blue or amber) and click the canvas to place training points, or press <strong>Sample data</strong>.</li>
              <li>Set the learning rate and press <strong>Train</strong>; the sigmoid is fit by gradient descent on cross-entropy.</li>
              <li>Watch the white decision line settle between the two clouds while the loss curve drops.</li>
              <li>Read the converged weights, loss and training accuracy. Add an outlier and re-train to see the boundary shift.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="sim">
          <div class="grid">
            <div class="panel">
              <h3>Sigmoid + cross-entropy &middot; gradient descent</h3>
              <canvas id="lgCanvas" width="760" height="500"></canvas>
              <div class="legend">
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#67e8f9;"></span>Class 0</span>
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#fbbf24;"></span>Class 1</span>
                <span>White line = decision boundary (p = 0.5)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="helptext"><strong>Click</strong> to place a point of the active class. Background shading is the predicted probability surface from a real forward pass.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="panel">
                <h3>Controls</h3>
                <div class="row"><label>Active</label>
                  <div class="seg" id="lgSeg">
                    <button class="on" data-cls="0">Class 0</button>
                    <button data-cls="1">Class 1</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row"><label>Learn rate</label><input type="range" id="lgLr" min="-2" max="1" step="0.05" value="-0.3"><span class="val" id="lgLrV">0.50</span></div>
                <div class="btns">
                  <button class="btn purple" id="lgRun">Train</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost" id="lgStep">Step</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="lgSeed">Sample data</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="lgClear">Clear points</button>
                </div>
                <div class="stats">
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">w1</div><div class="value cy" id="lgW1">0.000</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">w2</div><div class="value pu" id="lgW2">0.000</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">BCE loss</div><div class="value" id="lgL">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">accuracy</div><div class="value am" id="lgAcc">--</div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <canvas id="lgLoss" class="loss" width="320" height="120" style="margin-top:14px;"></canvas>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="logit"></div></div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="ref">
          <div class="prose"><h5>References</h5>
            <ul class="refs">
              <li><span class="who">Bishop, C. M.</span> <em>Pattern Recognition and Machine Learning</em>, Springer 2006 — Sec. 4.3, Probabilistic Discriminative Models.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Cox, D. R.</span> "The regression analysis of binary sequences", <em>J. Royal Statistical Society B</em>, 1958.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Murphy, K. P.</span> <em>Machine Learning: A Probabilistic Perspective</em>, MIT Press 2012 — Ch. 8.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <!-- EXP 3 : k-NN                                           -->
      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <div class="expbody" id="body-knn" style="display:none;">
        <div class="sect active" data-sect="aim">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Aim</h5>
            <p>To classify points by the majority vote of their k nearest neighbours under Euclidean distance, and to visualise how the decision regions and their smoothness change with k.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="theory">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Theory</h5>
            <p>k-Nearest-Neighbours is a non-parametric, "lazy" learner: there is no training phase. To classify a query point we measure its distance to every stored example, take the k closest, and assign the label held by the majority of them. Small k gives jagged, high-variance boundaries that hug noise; large k smooths the regions but can blur genuine class structure (bias-variance trade-off).</p>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">distance</span>  d(p, q) = sqrt( (p1-q1)^2 + (p2-q2)^2 )</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">prediction</span>  y_hat = mode of labels among the k smallest d(p, q)</div>
            <p>Cost is O(n) per query because every training point is examined; this is why k-NN scales poorly to huge datasets without spatial indexes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="proc">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Procedure</h5>
            <ol>
              <li>Select the active class and click to place training points, or press <strong>Sample data</strong>.</li>
              <li>Adjust <strong>k</strong> with the slider and watch the shaded decision regions reclassify live.</li>
              <li>Set k = 1 to see the Voronoi-like jagged boundary, then raise k to smooth it.</li>
              <li>Place an isolated point and observe how a larger k makes the model ignore it.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
