      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <!-- EXP 4 : k-MEANS                                        -->
      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <div class="expbody" id="body-km" style="display:none;">
        <div class="sect active" data-sect="aim">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Aim</h5>
            <p>To partition unlabelled 2-D points into k clusters using Lloyd's algorithm with k-means++ seeding, and to confirm that the within-cluster inertia decreases monotonically to convergence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="theory">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Theory</h5>
            <p>k-means is unsupervised: it seeks k centroids that minimise the total squared distance from each point to its nearest centroid (the inertia). Lloyd's algorithm alternates two steps — <strong>assign</strong> every point to its closest centroid, then <strong>update</strong> each centroid to the mean of its assigned points. Each step can only lower the inertia, so it converges, though only to a local optimum. k-means++ seeding spreads the initial centroids by distance weighting, which greatly improves the result.</p>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">inertia</span>  J = &Sigma;_i || x_i - &mu;_{c(i)} ||^2</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">assign</span>  c(i) = argmin_k || x_i - &mu;_k ||^2</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">update</span>  &mu;_k = mean of all x_i with c(i) = k</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="proc">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Procedure</h5>
            <ol>
              <li>Press <strong>Re-seed blobs</strong> to generate fresh Gaussian clusters.</li>
              <li>Set the number of clusters <strong>k</strong> and the point count.</li>
              <li>Press <strong>Run Lloyd</strong> to animate, or <strong>Step</strong> to watch one assign-update iteration at a time.</li>
              <li>Observe the inertia and "moved" distance drop each iteration until "converged" appears.</li>
              <li>Re-run a few times with the same k to see different local optima from different seeds.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="sim">
          <div class="grid">
            <div class="panel">
              <h3>Lloyd's algorithm</h3>
              <canvas id="kmCanvas" width="760" height="500"></canvas>
              <div class="helptext"><strong>Crosses</strong> are centroids; points recolour to their nearest centroid each iteration. Inertia is the total within-cluster squared distance — it only ever decreases.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="panel">
                <h3>Controls</h3>
                <div class="row"><label>Clusters k</label><input type="range" id="kmK" min="2" max="6" step="1" value="3"><span class="val" id="kmKV">3</span></div>
                <div class="row"><label>Points</label><input type="range" id="kmN" min="60" max="400" step="20" value="220"><span class="val" id="kmNV">220</span></div>
                <div class="btns">
                  <button class="btn purple" id="kmRun">Run Lloyd</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost" id="kmStep">Step</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="kmReseed">Re-seed blobs</button>
                </div>
                <div class="stats">
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">iteration</div><div class="value am" id="kmIt">0</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">inertia</div><div class="value pu" id="kmIn">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">moved</div><div class="value cy" id="kmMv">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">status</div><div class="value" id="kmSt">idle</div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="km"></div></div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="ref">
          <div class="prose"><h5>References</h5>
            <ul class="refs">
              <li><span class="who">Lloyd, S. P.</span> "Least squares quantization in PCM", <em>IEEE Trans. Information Theory</em>, 1982.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Arthur &amp; Vassilvitskii.</span> "k-means++: The advantages of careful seeding", <em>SODA</em>, 2007.</li>
              <li><span class="who">MacQueen, J.</span> "Some methods for classification and analysis of multivariate observations", <em>Berkeley Symp.</em>, 1967.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <!-- EXP 5 : DECISION TREE (NEW)                            -->
      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <div class="expbody" id="body-tree" style="display:none;">
        <div class="sect active" data-sect="aim">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Aim</h5>
            <p>To build a binary decision tree on 2-D labelled points by recursively choosing axis-aligned splits that maximise the impurity decrease (Gini or entropy), and to draw the resulting rectangular decision regions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="theory">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Theory</h5>
            <p>A decision tree partitions feature space with a sequence of axis-aligned thresholds. At each node the algorithm scans every feature and every candidate threshold and picks the split that most reduces impurity. Impurity measures how mixed the labels are in a node; both Gini and entropy are zero for a pure node and maximal for a 50/50 mix. The information gain is the parent impurity minus the size-weighted average impurity of the two children. Splitting stops at a maximum depth or when a node is pure.</p>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">Gini</span>  G = 1 - &Sigma;_k p_k^2</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">entropy</span>  H = - &Sigma;_k p_k&middot;log2(p_k)</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">gain</span>  IG = I(parent) - (n_L/n)&middot;I(L) - (n_R/n)&middot;I(R)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="proc">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Procedure</h5>
            <ol>
              <li>Select the active class and click to place points, or press <strong>Sample data</strong> for an XOR-like layout.</li>
              <li>Choose the impurity criterion (Gini or entropy) and the maximum depth.</li>
              <li>Press <strong>Build tree</strong>; the algorithm recursively finds the best split and shades each leaf rectangle by its majority class.</li>
              <li>Increase the depth to watch the boxy boundary carve finer regions and the training accuracy rise.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="sim">
          <div class="grid">
            <div class="panel">
              <h3>Recursive Gini / entropy splits</h3>
              <canvas id="trCanvas" width="760" height="500"></canvas>
              <div class="legend">
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#67e8f9;"></span>Class A</span>
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#fbbf24;"></span>Class B</span>
                <span>White lines = split thresholds; shading = leaf majority</span>
              </div>
              <div class="helptext"><strong>Click</strong> to add points, then <strong>Build tree</strong>. Every split is chosen by an exhaustive scan for maximum impurity decrease.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="panel">
                <h3>Controls</h3>
                <div class="row"><label>Active</label>
                  <div class="seg" id="trSeg">
                    <button class="on" data-cls="0">Class A</button>
                    <button data-cls="1">Class B</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row"><label>Criterion</label>
                  <div class="seg" id="trCrit">
                    <button class="on" data-crit="gini">Gini</button>
                    <button data-crit="entropy">Entropy</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row"><label>Max depth</label><input type="range" id="trDepth" min="1" max="6" step="1" value="3"><span class="val" id="trDepthV">3</span></div>
                <div class="btns">
                  <button class="btn purple" id="trBuild">Build tree</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost" id="trSeed">Sample data</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="trClear">Clear points</button>
                </div>
                <div class="stats">
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">leaves</div><div class="value cy" id="trLeaves">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">depth used</div><div class="value pu" id="trUsed">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">accuracy</div><div class="value am" id="trAcc">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">points</div><div class="value" id="trN">0</div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="tree"></div></div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="ref">
          <div class="prose"><h5>References</h5>
            <ul class="refs">
              <li><span class="who">Breiman, Friedman, Olshen &amp; Stone.</span> <em>Classification and Regression Trees (CART)</em>, Wadsworth 1984.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Quinlan, J. R.</span> "Induction of decision trees", <em>Machine Learning</em>, 1986 (ID3).</li>
              <li><span class="who">Hastie, Tibshirani &amp; Friedman.</span> <em>The Elements of Statistical Learning</em> — Sec. 9.2.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <!-- EXP 6 : PCA (NEW)                                      -->
      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <div class="expbody" id="body-pca" style="display:none;">
        <div class="sect active" data-sect="aim">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Aim</h5>
            <p>To compute the principal components of a 2-D point cloud from its covariance matrix using power iteration, and to draw the principal axes together with the projection of every point onto the first component.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="theory">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Theory</h5>
            <p>Principal Component Analysis finds the orthogonal directions of greatest variance in the data. After centering the points, we form the 2x2 covariance matrix; its eigenvectors are the principal axes and its eigenvalues are the variance captured along each. We extract the top eigenvector by <strong>power iteration</strong> — repeatedly multiplying a random vector by the covariance matrix and renormalising — then deflate to obtain the second. Projecting each point onto the first component reduces it from two dimensions to one while preserving as much spread as possible.</p>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">center</span>  x' = x - mean(x)</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">covariance</span>  C = (1/n) X'^T X'   (2x2)</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">power iter</span>  v &larr; C v / || C v ||   (repeat &rarr; top eigenvector)</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">explained</span>  ratio = &lambda;1 / (&lambda;1 + &lambda;2)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="proc">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Procedure</h5>
            <ol>
              <li>Press <strong>Sample data</strong> for an elongated tilted cloud, or click to add your own points.</li>
              <li>Press <strong>Run PCA</strong>; the covariance matrix is formed and power iteration converges on the principal axes.</li>
              <li>The long cyan arrow is PC1 (most variance), the short purple arrow is PC2; faint lines drop each point onto PC1.</li>
              <li>Read the eigenvalues and the variance explained by PC1. Stretch the cloud along one direction to drive that ratio toward 1.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="sim">
          <div class="grid">
            <div class="panel">
              <h3>Covariance &middot; power-iteration eigenvectors</h3>
              <canvas id="pcaCanvas" width="760" height="500"></canvas>
              <div class="legend">
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#67e8f9;"></span>PC1 axis</span>
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#a78bfa;"></span>PC2 axis</span>
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#fbbf24;"></span>projection onto PC1</span>
              </div>
              <div class="helptext"><strong>Click</strong> to add points, then <strong>Run PCA</strong>. The principal axes are real eigenvectors of the covariance matrix found by power iteration.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="panel">
                <h3>Controls</h3>
                <div class="btns">
                  <button class="btn purple" id="pcaRun">Run PCA</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost" id="pcaSeed">Sample data</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="pcaClear">Clear points</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="pcaProj">Toggle projection</button>
                </div>
                <div class="stats">
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">&lambda;1 (PC1)</div><div class="value cy" id="pcaL1">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">&lambda;2 (PC2)</div><div class="value pu" id="pcaL2">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">explained</div><div class="value am" id="pcaExp">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">iters</div><div class="value" id="pcaIt">--</div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="helptext">PC1 angle: <code id="pcaAng">--</code>. The two axes are orthogonal by construction.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="pca"></div></div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="ref">
          <div class="prose"><h5>References</h5>
            <ul class="refs">
              <li><span class="who">Pearson, K.</span> "On lines and planes of closest fit to systems of points in space", <em>Phil. Mag.</em>, 1901.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Jolliffe, I. T.</span> <em>Principal Component Analysis</em>, 2nd ed., Springer 2002.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Golub &amp; Van Loan.</span> <em>Matrix Computations</em>, 4th ed., JHU Press 2013 — power iteration.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <!-- EXP 7 : NEURAL NETWORK                                 -->
      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <div class="expbody" id="body-nn" style="display:none;">
        <div class="sect active" data-sect="aim">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Aim</h5>
            <p>To train a multilayer perceptron (2 &rarr; 8 &rarr; 8 &rarr; 1) with two tanh hidden layers and a sigmoid output by full backpropagation, and to watch it learn a non-linear decision boundary on XOR, circles, moons or spiral data.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="theory">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Theory</h5>
            <p>A multilayer perceptron stacks linear maps and non-linear activations so it can represent decision boundaries no single line could. The forward pass computes activations layer by layer; backpropagation then applies the chain rule backwards to obtain the gradient of the loss with respect to every weight. For the sigmoid output with binary cross-entropy the output error simplifies neatly to (prediction - target). Xavier initialisation keeps the initial signal variance stable across layers.</p>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">forward</span>  a^(l) = f( W^(l) a^(l-1) + b^(l) ),  f = tanh (hidden), &sigma; (output)</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">output delta</span>  &delta;^(L) = a^(L) - y</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">hidden delta</span>  &delta;^(l) = (W^(l+1)^T &delta;^(l+1)) &odot; (1 - a^(l)^2)</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">gradient</span>  dL/dW^(l) = &delta;^(l) (a^(l-1))^T</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="proc">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Procedure</h5>
            <ol>
              <li>Pick a <strong>dataset</strong> (XOR, two circles, two moons or spiral).</li>
              <li>Set the learning rate and press <strong>Train</strong> to run backprop with full-batch gradient descent.</li>
              <li>Watch the coloured prediction surface bend to separate the classes while the BCE loss falls and accuracy climbs.</li>
              <li>Press <strong>Reset</strong> to re-initialise the weights; try the spiral, which needs many epochs and the right learning rate.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="sim">
          <div class="grid">
            <div class="panel">
              <h3>2 &rarr; 8 &rarr; 8 &rarr; 1 MLP &middot; backpropagation</h3>
              <canvas id="nnCanvas" width="760" height="440"></canvas>
              <canvas id="nnLoss" class="loss" width="760" height="150"></canvas>
              <div class="helptext">A real multilayer perceptron with two tanh hidden layers and a sigmoid output, trained by backprop + full-batch gradient descent. The background shading is the network's live prediction surface; the loss is binary cross-entropy.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="panel">
                <h3>Controls</h3>
                <div class="row"><label>Dataset</label>
                  <select id="nnData">
                    <option value="xor">XOR</option>
                    <option value="circles">Two circles</option>
                    <option value="moons">Two moons</option>
                    <option value="spiral">Spiral</option>
                  </select>
                </div>
                <div class="row"><label>Learn rate</label><input type="range" id="nnLr" min="-3" max="0.3" step="0.05" value="-0.7"><span class="val" id="nnLrV">0.20</span></div>
                <div class="btns">
                  <button class="btn purple" id="nnRun">Train</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost" id="nnReset">Reset</button>
                </div>
                <div class="stats">
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">epoch</div><div class="value am" id="nnE">0</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">BCE loss</div><div class="value pu" id="nnL">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">accuracy</div><div class="value cy" id="nnAcc">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">status</div><div class="value" id="nnSt">idle</div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="helptext">Weights use Xavier initialisation. Decision boundary is recomputed on a coarse grid each frame through a real forward pass.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="nn"></div></div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="ref">
          <div class="prose"><h5>References</h5>
            <ul class="refs">
              <li><span class="who">Rumelhart, Hinton &amp; Williams.</span> "Learning representations by back-propagating errors", <em>Nature</em>, 1986.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Glorot &amp; Bengio.</span> "Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks", <em>AISTATS</em>, 2010 (Xavier init).</li>
              <li><span class="who">Goodfellow, Bengio &amp; Courville.</span> <em>Deep Learning</em>, MIT Press 2016 — Ch. 6.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <!-- EXP 8 : OPTIMIZERS (NEW)                               -->
      <!-- ====================================================== -->
      <div class="expbody" id="body-opt" style="display:none;">
        <div class="sect active" data-sect="aim">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Aim</h5>
            <p>To compare three gradient-descent optimizers — plain SGD, SGD with momentum, and Adam — by watching their paths descend a 2-D loss surface from the same start, and to compare their loss-versus-iteration curves.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="theory">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Theory</h5>
            <p>All three optimizers follow the negative gradient, but they differ in how they smooth and scale the step. Plain SGD takes a fixed multiple of the gradient and oscillates in narrow valleys. Momentum accumulates an exponentially-decayed velocity, damping oscillation and accelerating along consistent directions. Adam keeps running averages of both the gradient (first moment) and its square (second moment), bias-corrects them, and divides the step by the root of the second moment — giving an adaptive per-parameter learning rate.</p>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">SGD</span>  &theta; &larr; &theta; - &eta; g</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">momentum</span>  v &larr; &beta; v + g ;  &theta; &larr; &theta; - &eta; v</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl">Adam</span>  m &larr; &beta;1 m + (1-&beta;1) g ;  s &larr; &beta;2 s + (1-&beta;2) g^2</div>
            <div class="eq"><span class="lbl"></span>  &theta; &larr; &theta; - &eta;&middot;m_hat / (sqrt(s_hat) + &epsilon;)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="proc">
          <div class="prose"><h5>Procedure</h5>
            <ol>
              <li>Choose a loss surface (a stretched bowl, a saddle, or Rosenbrock's banana valley).</li>
              <li>Click anywhere on the contour map to set a common starting point for all three optimizers.</li>
              <li>Set the base learning rate and press <strong>Run</strong>; the three paths descend simultaneously.</li>
              <li>Compare the trajectories on the contours and the loss curves below — note how Adam and momentum usually reach the minimum first.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="sim">
          <div class="grid">
            <div class="panel">
              <h3>SGD vs Momentum vs Adam on a 2-D surface</h3>
              <canvas id="optCanvas" width="760" height="440"></canvas>
              <canvas id="optLoss" class="loss" width="760" height="150"></canvas>
              <div class="legend">
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#67e8f9;"></span>SGD</span>
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#fbbf24;"></span>Momentum</span>
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#a78bfa;"></span>Adam</span>
                <span><span class="dot" style="background:#86efac;"></span>minimum</span>
              </div>
              <div class="helptext"><strong>Click</strong> the contour map to set the start point. Each optimizer descends the real analytic gradient of the chosen surface.</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="panel">
                <h3>Controls</h3>
                <div class="row"><label>Surface</label>
                  <select id="optSurf">
                    <option value="bowl">Stretched bowl</option>
                    <option value="saddle">Saddle</option>
                    <option value="rosen">Rosenbrock</option>
                  </select>
                </div>
                <div class="row"><label>Learn rate</label><input type="range" id="optLr" min="-3" max="-0.3" step="0.05" value="-1.4"><span class="val" id="optLrV">0.04</span></div>
                <div class="btns">
                  <button class="btn purple" id="optRun">Run</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost" id="optStep">Step</button>
                  <button class="btn ghost full" id="optReset">Reset paths</button>
                </div>
                <div class="stats">
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">iteration</div><div class="value am" id="optIt">0</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">SGD loss</div><div class="value cy" id="optLs">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">Mom loss</div><div class="value am" id="optLm">--</div></div>
                  <div class="stat"><div class="label">Adam loss</div><div class="value pu" id="optLa">--</div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="opt"></div></div>
        <div class="sect" data-sect="ref">
          <div class="prose"><h5>References</h5>
            <ul class="refs">
              <li><span class="who">Kingma &amp; Ba.</span> "Adam: A method for stochastic optimization", <em>ICLR</em>, 2015.</li>
              <li><span class="who">Polyak, B. T.</span> "Some methods of speeding up the convergence of iteration methods", <em>USSR Comput. Math.</em>, 1964 (momentum).</li>
              <li><span class="who">Ruder, S.</span> "An overview of gradient descent optimization algorithms", arXiv:1609.04747, 2016.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</main>

<script is:inline>
(function(){
  "use strict";

  // ---------- shared helpers ----------
  function rnd(a, b){ return a + Math.random() * (b - a); }
  function gauss(){ // Box-Muller standard normal
    var u = 1 - Math.random(), v = Math.random();
    return Math.sqrt(-2 * Math.log(u)) * Math.cos(2 * Math.PI * v);
  }
  function clamp(x, lo, hi){ return x < lo ? lo : (x > hi ? hi : x); }
  function fmt(x, d){ if (!isFinite(x)) return "--"; return x.toFixed(d == null ? 3 : d); }

  // canvas pixel-coordinate helper (account for CSS scaling)
  function evtXY(canvas, e){
    var r = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
    return { x: (e.clientX - r.left) * (canvas.width / r.width), y: (e.clientY - r.top) * (canvas.height / r.height) };
  }

  var EXP_META = {
    reg:   ["Linear regression via gradient descent", "Experiment 01 · supervised learning · mean-squared-error minimisation"],
    logit: ["Logistic regression", "Experiment 02 · binary classification · sigmoid + cross-entropy"],
    knn:   ["k-NN classification with decision regions", "Experiment 03 · non-parametric · Euclidean majority vote"],
    km:    ["k-means clustering", "Experiment 04 · unsupervised · Lloyd's algorithm + k-means++"],
    tree:  ["Decision tree classifier", "Experiment 05 · recursive impurity splits · Gini / entropy"],
    pca:   ["PCA dimensionality reduction", "Experiment 06 · covariance · power-iteration eigenvectors"],
    nn:    ["Neural network (MLP backprop)", "Experiment 07 · 2-8-8-1 · tanh hidden + sigmoid output"],
    opt:   ["Gradient-descent optimizers compared", "Experiment 08 · SGD vs momentum vs Adam"]
  };

  // ---------- experiment (sidebar) switching ----------
  var explist = document.getElementById("explist").querySelectorAll(".exitem");
  var bodies = {};
  ["reg","logit","knn","km","tree","pca","nn","opt"].forEach(function(id){ bodies[id] = document.getElementById("body-" + id); });

  function onShow(id){
    if (id === "reg") REG.draw();
    if (id === "logit") LOGIT.render();
    if (id === "knn") KNN.render();
    if (id === "km") KM.draw();
    if (id === "tree") TREE.render();
    if (id === "pca") PCA.draw();
    if (id === "nn") NN.draw();
    if (id === "opt") OPT.draw();
  }

  function switchExp(id){
    for (var k in bodies) bodies[k].style.display = (k === id) ? "block" : "none";
    for (var i = 0; i < explist.length; i++) explist[i].classList.toggle("active", explist[i].getAttribute("data-exp") === id);
    var m = EXP_META[id];
    document.getElementById("expTitle").textContent = m[0];
    document.getElementById("expSub").innerHTML = m[1];
    // reset section tabs to Aim for the newly shown body
    resetSections(id);
    onShow(id);
  }
  for (var e = 0; e < explist.length; e++){
    (function(btn){ btn.addEventListener("click", function(){ switchExp(btn.getAttribute("data-exp")); }); })(explist[e]);
  }

  // ---------- section (tab) switching, applies to the currently visible body ----------
  var tabs = document.getElementById("tabs").querySelectorAll(".tab");
  function currentExp(){ for (var k in bodies) if (bodies[k].style.display !== "none") return k; return "reg"; }
  function showSection(name){
    var id = currentExp();
    var body = bodies[id];
    var sects = body.querySelectorAll(".sect");
    for (var i = 0; i < sects.length; i++) sects[i].classList.toggle("active", sects[i].getAttribute("data-sect") === name);
    for (var t = 0; t < tabs.length; t++) tabs[t].classList.toggle("active", tabs[t].getAttribute("data-tab") === name);
    if (name === "sim") onShow(id);
    if (name === "quiz") buildQuiz(id);
  }
  function resetSections(id){
    var body = bodies[id];
    var sects = body.querySelectorAll(".sect");
    for (var i = 0; i < sects.length; i++) sects[i].classList.toggle("active", sects[i].getAttribute("data-sect") === "aim");
    for (var t = 0; t < tabs.length; t++) tabs[t].classList.toggle("active", tabs[t].getAttribute("data-tab") === "aim");
  }
  for (var ti = 0; ti < tabs.length; ti++){
    (function(tb){ tb.addEventListener("click", function(){ showSection(tb.getAttribute("data-tab")); }); })(tabs[ti]);
  }

  // ======================================================================
  // SELF-ASSESSMENT QUIZZES
  // ======================================================================
  var QUIZ = {
    reg: [
      { q: "Why is mean-squared error a convenient loss for fitting a line by gradient descent?",
        opts: ["It is convex and differentiable, so gradient descent reaches the global minimum", "It ignores outliers completely", "It has no gradient, so no learning rate is needed", "It can only be minimised in closed form"],
        a: 0, ex: "MSE is a smooth convex bowl in (w, b); its single minimum is reachable by following the gradient." },
      { q: "If the learning rate is set far too large, what typically happens to the loss?",
        opts: ["It decreases faster and is always better", "It overshoots the minimum and can diverge (grow without bound)", "It stays exactly constant", "It becomes negative"],
        a: 1, ex: "Too-large steps jump past the minimum, so the loss can oscillate or blow up instead of converging." },
      { q: "An R² value of 1.0 means:",
        opts: ["The model explains none of the variance", "The model perfectly fits every point (zero residual)", "The slope is exactly zero", "The data has no variance"],
        a: 1, ex: "R² = 1 - SS_res/SS_tot; SS_res = 0 gives R² = 1, a perfect fit." },
      { q: "The gradient dL/db for MSE is proportional to:",
        opts: ["the sum of the inputs x", "the mean prediction error (y_hat - y)", "the square of the weights", "a constant independent of the data"],
        a: 1, ex: "dL/db = (2/n) Σ (y_hat - y): it is the averaged signed error." }
    ],
    logit: [
      { q: "What does the sigmoid function guarantee about the model output?",
        opts: ["It is always an integer", "It lies strictly between 0 and 1, so it can be read as a probability", "It equals the raw linear score", "It is always greater than 1"],
        a: 1, ex: "σ(z) = 1/(1+e^-z) maps any real z into (0, 1)." },
      { q: "The decision boundary of logistic regression in this 2-D demo is:",
        opts: ["a circle", "always a straight line (where z = 0)", "a parabola", "a random curve"],
        a: 1, ex: "The model is linear in the features, so p = 0.5 (z = 0) is a straight line." },
      { q: "The gradient of binary cross-entropy with respect to a weight is proportional to:",
        opts: ["(p - y) times the input feature", "the square of the prediction", "the entropy of the labels", "a constant"],
        a: 0, ex: "dL/dw_j = (1/n) Σ (p_i - y_i) x_ij — the same neat error×input form as linear regression." },
      { q: "Why prefer cross-entropy over squared error for classification?",
        opts: ["It is always smaller", "It penalises confident wrong predictions strongly and gives well-behaved gradients with the sigmoid", "It removes the need for a bias term", "It makes the boundary non-linear"],
        a: 1, ex: "Log-loss grows sharply as a confident prediction becomes wrong and pairs cleanly with the sigmoid derivative." }
    ],
    knn: [
      { q: "k-NN is called a 'lazy' learner because:",
        opts: ["it always predicts the majority class", "it does no work at training time and defers all computation to query time", "it cannot handle more than two classes", "it discards the training data"],
        a: 1, ex: "There is no fitted model; every query scans the stored examples." },
      { q: "Increasing k generally makes the decision boundary:",
        opts: ["more jagged and noisy", "smoother, with lower variance but higher bias", "always more accurate", "exactly the same"],
        a: 1, ex: "Averaging over more neighbours smooths the regions — the classic bias-variance trade-off." },
      { q: "Which distance does this experiment use to find neighbours?",
        opts: ["Manhattan (L1)", "Euclidean (L2)", "Cosine", "Hamming"],
        a: 1, ex: "It ranks neighbours by squared Euclidean distance (x1-x2)² + (y1-y2)²." },
      { q: "The query cost of basic k-NN per prediction is:",
        opts: ["O(1)", "O(log n)", "O(n) — it compares against every training point", "O(n²)"],
        a: 2, ex: "Without a spatial index it measures distance to all n stored points." }
    ],
    km: [
      { q: "What quantity does Lloyd's algorithm decrease at every step?",
        opts: ["the number of clusters", "the within-cluster inertia (sum of squared distances)", "the number of points", "the learning rate"],
        a: 1, ex: "Both the assign and update steps can only lower J = Σ ||x - μ||²." },
      { q: "Why use k-means++ seeding instead of purely random centroids?",
        opts: ["It guarantees the global optimum", "It spreads initial centroids by distance, reducing bad local optima", "It removes the need to iterate", "It changes the number of clusters automatically"],
        a: 1, ex: "Distance-weighted seeding starts the centroids far apart, giving much better and more reliable results." },
      { q: "k-means is guaranteed to converge to:",
        opts: ["the global optimum every time", "a local optimum (depends on initialisation)", "never converges", "a saddle point"],
        a: 1, ex: "It monotonically decreases inertia and stops, but the result depends on the starting centroids." },
      { q: "A point is assigned to a cluster based on:",
        opts: ["its label", "the nearest centroid by squared distance", "a random draw", "its index"],
        a: 1, ex: "Assignment is c(i) = argmin_k ||x_i - μ_k||²." }
    ],
    tree: [
      { q: "The Gini impurity of a node is zero when:",
        opts: ["the node has exactly two classes in equal numbers", "the node is pure (all points share one class)", "the node is empty", "the depth is maximal"],
        a: 1, ex: "G = 1 - Σ p_k² = 0 only when one class has probability 1." },
      { q: "At each node the tree chooses the split that:",
        opts: ["uses the deepest feature", "maximises the impurity decrease (information gain)", "minimises the number of points", "is always vertical"],
        a: 1, ex: "It scans features and thresholds for the largest IG = I(parent) - weighted I(children)." },
      { q: "Decision-tree boundaries on 2-D data are:",
        opts: ["smooth curves", "axis-aligned rectangles (boxy)", "circles", "always diagonal"],
        a: 1, ex: "Each split is a single-feature threshold, so regions are axis-parallel boxes." },
      { q: "Allowing unlimited depth tends to cause:",
        opts: ["underfitting", "overfitting — the tree memorises noise", "faster prediction", "lower training accuracy"],
        a: 1, ex: "Deep trees can isolate every point, fitting noise; depth limits regularise them." }
    ],
    pca: [
      { q: "The first principal component points in the direction of:",
        opts: ["least variance", "greatest variance in the data", "the mean", "the smallest eigenvalue"],
        a: 1, ex: "PC1 is the top eigenvector of the covariance matrix — the axis of maximum variance." },
      { q: "Power iteration finds the top eigenvector by:",
        opts: ["solving a linear system once", "repeatedly multiplying a vector by C and renormalising", "sorting the data", "computing the median"],
        a: 1, ex: "Repeated multiplication by C amplifies the dominant eigen-direction; renormalising keeps it unit length." },
      { q: "Before computing the covariance matrix, PCA requires that the data be:",
        opts: ["sorted", "centered (mean subtracted)", "labelled", "made positive"],
        a: 1, ex: "Covariance is defined about the mean, so the cloud is shifted to the origin first." },
      { q: "The two principal axes returned by PCA are:",
        opts: ["parallel", "orthogonal to each other", "always horizontal and vertical", "identical"],
        a: 1, ex: "Eigenvectors of a symmetric covariance matrix are orthogonal." }
    ],
    nn: [
      { q: "Why does the MLP need non-linear activations like tanh?",
        opts: ["to make training slower", "without them, stacked linear layers collapse to a single linear map", "to remove the need for weights", "to guarantee convergence"],
        a: 1, ex: "Composition of linear maps is still linear; non-linearities let the net form curved boundaries (e.g. XOR)." },
      { q: "For a sigmoid output with binary cross-entropy, the output-layer error δ equals:",
        opts: ["target - input", "prediction - target (a - y)", "the squared error", "always zero"],
        a: 1, ex: "The sigmoid and BCE derivatives combine to give the clean form δ = a - y." },
      { q: "Backpropagation is essentially:",
        opts: ["random search over weights", "the chain rule applied backwards through the layers", "a sorting algorithm", "a closed-form matrix inverse"],
        a: 1, ex: "It propagates the loss gradient layer by layer using the chain rule." },
      { q: "Xavier (Glorot) initialisation is used to:",
        opts: ["set all weights to zero", "keep the signal variance roughly stable across layers at the start", "make the network deterministic", "remove the bias terms"],
        a: 1, ex: "It scales initial weights by 1/√(n_in+n_out) so activations neither vanish nor explode early on." }
    ],
    opt: [
      { q: "What does momentum add to plain SGD?",
        opts: ["a smaller learning rate", "an exponentially-decayed velocity that damps oscillation and accelerates consistent directions", "random noise", "a second loss function"],
        a: 1, ex: "v ← βv + g accumulates past gradients, smoothing the path through narrow valleys." },
      { q: "Adam adapts the step size per parameter by dividing by:",
        opts: ["the number of iterations", "the square root of a running average of squared gradients", "the learning rate squared", "the loss value"],
        a: 1, ex: "It scales by 1/√(s_hat), the second-moment estimate, giving per-parameter rates." },
      { q: "On a stretched (ill-conditioned) bowl, plain SGD tends to:",
        opts: ["go straight to the minimum", "oscillate across the steep direction and crawl along the shallow one", "diverge immediately", "ignore the gradient"],
        a: 1, ex: "Equal steps in both directions bounce across the narrow axis while creeping along the flat one." },
      { q: "Adam's bias correction (m_hat, s_hat) is important because:",
        opts: ["the moment estimates start at zero and are biased low early in training", "it changes the loss function", "it removes the learning rate", "it makes Adam identical to SGD"],
        a: 0, ex: "Initialising the moments at zero biases them toward zero; dividing by (1-β^t) corrects the early steps." }
    ]
  };
  var quizBuilt = {};
  function buildQuiz(id){
    if (quizBuilt[id]) return;
    var host = bodies[id].querySelector('.quiz');
    if (!host) return;
    var qs = QUIZ[id]; var html = "";
    for (var i = 0; i < qs.length; i++){
      html += '<div class="q" data-qi="' + i + '"><div class="qq">' + (i + 1) + ". " + qs[i].q + '</div>';
      for (var j = 0; j < qs[i].opts.length; j++){
        html += '<label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="' + id + '_q' + i + '" value="' + j + '"><span>' + qs[i].opts[j] + '</span></label>';
      }
      html += '<div class="expl"></div></div>';
    }
    html += '<div class="quizbar"><button class="btn" data-check="' + id + '">Check answers</button><span class="quizscore" data-score="' + id + '"></span></div>';
    host.innerHTML = html;
    host.querySelector('[data-check="' + id + '"]').addEventListener("click", function(){ checkQuiz(id, host); });
    quizBuilt[id] = true;
  }
  function checkQuiz(id, host){
    var qs = QUIZ[id]; var correct = 0;
    var blocks = host.querySelectorAll(".q");
    for (var i = 0; i < blocks.length; i++){
      var opts = blocks[i].querySelectorAll(".opt");
      var chosen = -1;
      for (var j = 0; j < opts.length; j++){
        opts[j].classList.remove("correct", "wrong");
        var radio = opts[j].querySelector("input");
        if (radio.checked) chosen = j;
      }
      for (var k = 0; k < opts.length; k++){
        if (k === qs[i].a) opts[k].classList.add("correct");
        else if (k === chosen) opts[k].classList.add("wrong");
      }
      if (chosen === qs[i].a) correct++;
      var ex = blocks[i].querySelector(".expl");
      ex.innerHTML = "<b>" + (chosen === qs[i].a ? "Correct." : "Answer: " + (qs[i].a + 1) + ".") + "</b> " + qs[i].ex;
      ex.classList.add("show");
    }
    host.querySelector('[data-score="' + id + '"]').textContent = "Score: " + correct + " / " + qs.length;
  }

  // ======================================================================
  // 1. LINEAR REGRESSION via GRADIENT DESCENT  (preserved verbatim)
  // ======================================================================
  var REG = (function(){
    var cv = document.getElementById("regCanvas"), ctx = cv.getContext("2d");
    var lc = document.getElementById("regLoss"), lctx = lc.getContext("2d");
    var W = cv.width, H = cv.height;
    var pts = [];           // data-space points {x:0..1, y:0..1}
    var w = 0, b = 0;       // model params (in normalised space)
    var epoch = 0, loss = NaN, lossHist = [], running = false, raf = null;
    var lr = 0.05;

    function lrFromSlider(){ lr = Math.pow(10, parseFloat(document.getElementById("regLr").value)); document.getElementById("regLrV").textContent = lr < 0.001 ? lr.toExponential(1) : fmt(lr, 4); }

    // map data [0,1] -> pixels
    function px(x){ return 40 + x * (W - 70); }
    function py(y){ return (H - 40) - y * (H - 70); }
    function invX(sx){ return (sx - 40) / (W - 70); }
    function invY(sy){ return ((H - 40) - sy) / (H - 70); }

    function reset(){ w = rnd(-0.5, 0.5); b = rnd(0.2, 0.6); epoch = 0; loss = NaN; lossHist = []; }

    function computeLoss(){
      if (!pts.length) return NaN;
      var s = 0;
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){ var e = (w * pts[i].x + b) - pts[i].y; s += e * e; }
      return s / pts.length;
    }

    function step(){
      if (pts.length < 2) return;
      // gradients of MSE = (1/n) sum (w x + b - y)^2
      var gw = 0, gb = 0, n = pts.length;
      for (var i = 0; i < n; i++){
        var pr = w * pts[i].x + b;
        var err = pr - pts[i].y;
        gw += err * pts[i].x;
        gb += err;
      }
      gw = (2 / n) * gw; gb = (2 / n) * gb;
      w -= lr * gw; b -= lr * gb;
      epoch++;
      loss = computeLoss();
      lossHist.push(loss);
      if (lossHist.length > 600) lossHist.shift();
    }

    function r2(){
      if (pts.length < 2) return NaN;
      var mean = 0, i; for (i = 0; i < pts.length; i++) mean += pts[i].y; mean /= pts.length;
      var ssTot = 0, ssRes = 0;
      for (i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
        var pr = w * pts[i].x + b;
        ssRes += (pts[i].y - pr) * (pts[i].y - pr);
        ssTot += (pts[i].y - mean) * (pts[i].y - mean);
      }
      return ssTot === 0 ? 0 : 1 - ssRes / ssTot;
    }

    function grid(){
      ctx.strokeStyle = "#1a1c24"; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      for (var g = 0; g <= 10; g++){
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(px(g/10), py(0)); ctx.lineTo(px(g/10), py(1)); ctx.stroke();
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(px(0), py(g/10)); ctx.lineTo(px(1), py(g/10)); ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.strokeStyle = "#2a2a35"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(px(0), py(0)); ctx.lineTo(px(1), py(0)); ctx.stroke();
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(px(0), py(0)); ctx.lineTo(px(0), py(1)); ctx.stroke();
    }

    function draw(){
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H);
      ctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
      grid();
      // fitted line
      if (pts.length >= 1){
        ctx.strokeStyle = "#a78bfa"; ctx.lineWidth = 2.5;
        ctx.beginPath();
        var y0 = w * 0 + b, y1 = w * 1 + b;
        ctx.moveTo(px(0), py(clamp(y0, -0.5, 1.5))); ctx.lineTo(px(1), py(clamp(y1, -0.5, 1.5)));
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      // residuals + points
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
        var pr = w * pts[i].x + b;
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(252,165,165,0.35)"; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(px(pts[i].x), py(pts[i].y)); ctx.lineTo(px(pts[i].x), py(pr)); ctx.stroke();
        ctx.fillStyle = "#67e8f9";
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(px(pts[i].x), py(pts[i].y), 4, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill();
      }
      drawLoss();
      document.getElementById("regW").textContent = fmt(w, 3);
      document.getElementById("regB").textContent = fmt(b, 3);
      document.getElementById("regL").textContent = isFinite(loss) ? fmt(loss, 5) : "--";
      document.getElementById("regE").textContent = epoch;
      var r = r2(); document.getElementById("regR2").textContent = isFinite(r) ? fmt(r, 4) : "--";
    }

    function drawLoss(){
      lctx.clearRect(0, 0, lc.width, lc.height);
      lctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; lctx.fillRect(0, 0, lc.width, lc.height);
      lctx.fillStyle = "#9aa0aa"; lctx.font = "10px ui-monospace";
      lctx.fillText("MSE loss", 8, 14);
      if (lossHist.length < 2) return;
      var mx = 0; for (var i = 0; i < lossHist.length; i++) if (lossHist[i] > mx) mx = lossHist[i];
      if (mx <= 0) mx = 1;
      lctx.strokeStyle = "#fbbf24"; lctx.lineWidth = 2; lctx.beginPath();
      for (var j = 0; j < lossHist.length; j++){
        var x = 8 + j / (lossHist.length - 1) * (lc.width - 16);
        var y = lc.height - 12 - (lossHist[j] / mx) * (lc.height - 30);
        if (j === 0) lctx.moveTo(x, y); else lctx.lineTo(x, y);
      }
      lctx.stroke();
    }

    function loop(){ if (!running) return; for (var s = 0; s < 3; s++) step(); draw(); if (loss < 1e-7 && epoch > 30){ running = false; document.getElementById("regRun").textContent = "Train"; return; } raf = requestAnimationFrame(loop); }

    function seedSample(){
      pts = [];
      var tw = rnd(0.5, 1.4), tb = rnd(0.05, 0.4);
      for (var i = 0; i < 26; i++){ var x = rnd(0.04, 0.96); var y = clamp(tw * x + tb + gauss() * 0.06, 0.01, 0.99); pts.push({ x: x, y: y }); }
      reset(); draw();
    }

    cv.addEventListener("click", function(e){
      var p = evtXY(cv, e);
      var x = invX(p.x), y = invY(p.y);
      if (x < -0.02 || x > 1.02 || y < -0.02 || y > 1.02) return;
      pts.push({ x: clamp(x, 0, 1), y: clamp(y, 0, 1) });
      loss = computeLoss(); draw();
    });
    document.getElementById("regLr").addEventListener("input", lrFromSlider);
    document.getElementById("regRun").addEventListener("click", function(){
      if (pts.length < 2) return;
      running = !running; this.textContent = running ? "Pause" : "Train";
      if (running) loop();
    });
    document.getElementById("regStep").addEventListener("click", function(){ for (var s = 0; s < 5; s++) step(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("regSeed").addEventListener("click", seedSample);
    document.getElementById("regClear").addEventListener("click", function(){ pts = []; reset(); draw(); });

    lrFromSlider(); reset(); seedSample();
    return { draw: draw };
  })();

  // ======================================================================
  // 2. LOGISTIC REGRESSION (NEW): sigmoid + BCE, gradient descent
  // ======================================================================
  var LOGIT = (function(){
    var cv = document.getElementById("lgCanvas"), ctx = cv.getContext("2d");
    var lc = document.getElementById("lgLoss"), lctx = lc.getContext("2d");
    var W = cv.width, H = cv.height;
    var pts = [];                    // {x:0..1, y:0..1, c:0|1}
    var w1 = 0, w2 = 0, b = 0;       // weights in normalised feature space
    var loss = NaN, acc = NaN, lossHist = [], running = false, raf = null;
    var lr = 0.5, activeClass = 0;

    function sigmoid(z){ if (z < -30) return 0; if (z > 30) return 1; return 1 / (1 + Math.exp(-z)); }
    function lrFromSlider(){ lr = Math.pow(10, parseFloat(document.getElementById("lgLr").value)); document.getElementById("lgLrV").textContent = fmt(lr, lr < 0.1 ? 3 : 2); }
    function reset(){ w1 = rnd(-0.4, 0.4); w2 = rnd(-0.4, 0.4); b = 0; loss = NaN; acc = NaN; lossHist = []; }

    function feat(p){ return [(p.x - 0.5) * 4, (p.y - 0.5) * 4]; } // scale to ~[-2,2]

    function step(){
      if (pts.length < 2) return;
      var gw1 = 0, gw2 = 0, gb = 0, n = pts.length, totLoss = 0, correct = 0;
      for (var i = 0; i < n; i++){
        var f = feat(pts[i]);
        var z = w1 * f[0] + w2 * f[1] + b;
        var p = sigmoid(z), y = pts[i].c;
        var err = p - y;
        gw1 += err * f[0]; gw2 += err * f[1]; gb += err;
        var pc = clamp(p, 1e-7, 1 - 1e-7);
        totLoss += -(y * Math.log(pc) + (1 - y) * Math.log(1 - pc));
        if ((p > 0.5 ? 1 : 0) === y) correct++;
      }
      w1 -= lr * gw1 / n; w2 -= lr * gw2 / n; b -= lr * gb / n;
      loss = totLoss / n; acc = correct / n;
      lossHist.push(loss); if (lossHist.length > 600) lossHist.shift();
    }

    function recompute(){
      if (pts.length < 1){ loss = NaN; acc = NaN; return; }
      var n = pts.length, totLoss = 0, correct = 0;
      for (var i = 0; i < n; i++){
        var f = feat(pts[i]);
        var p = sigmoid(w1 * f[0] + w2 * f[1] + b), y = pts[i].c;
        var pc = clamp(p, 1e-7, 1 - 1e-7);
        totLoss += -(y * Math.log(pc) + (1 - y) * Math.log(1 - pc));
        if ((p > 0.5 ? 1 : 0) === y) correct++;
      }
      loss = totLoss / n; acc = correct / n;
    }

    function render(){
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H); ctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
      // probability surface
      var cell = 10, img = ctx.createImageData(W, H);
      for (var gy = 0; gy < H; gy += cell){
        for (var gx = 0; gx < W; gx += cell){
          var nx = (gx + cell / 2) / W, ny = (gy + cell / 2) / H;
          var f = feat({ x: nx, y: ny });
          var p = sigmoid(w1 * f[0] + w2 * f[1] + b);
          var t = clamp((p - 0.5) * 2, -1, 1), rr, gg, bb;
          if (t >= 0){ rr = 80 + t * 171; gg = 60 + t * 131; bb = 30; }
          else { var u = -t; rr = 40; gg = 60 + u * 172; bb = 60 + u * 189; }
          for (var yy = gy; yy < gy + cell && yy < H; yy++){
            for (var xx = gx; xx < gx + cell && xx < W; xx++){
              var idx = (yy * W + xx) * 4;
              img.data[idx] = rr; img.data[idx + 1] = gg; img.data[idx + 2] = bb; img.data[idx + 3] = 60;
            }
          }
        }
      }
      ctx.putImageData(img, 0, 0);
      // decision boundary: w1*f1 + w2*f2 + b = 0, with f = (x-0.5)*4
      // => w1*(x-0.5)*4 + w2*(y-0.5)*4 + b = 0. Solve for y across x in [0,1].
      if (Math.abs(w2) > 1e-6){
        ctx.strokeStyle = "#ffffff"; ctx.lineWidth = 2; ctx.beginPath();
        var drawn = false;
        for (var sx = 0; sx <= 1.0001; sx += 0.02){
          var fx = (sx - 0.5) * 4;
          var fy = -(w1 * fx + b) / w2;
          var yy2 = fy / 4 + 0.5;
          var X = sx * W, Y = yy2 * H;
          if (!drawn){ ctx.moveTo(X, Y); drawn = true; } else ctx.lineTo(X, Y);
        }
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      // points
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
        ctx.fillStyle = pts[i].c === 1 ? "#fbbf24" : "#67e8f9";
        ctx.strokeStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.4;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(pts[i].x * W, pts[i].y * H, 5, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
      }
      drawLoss();
      document.getElementById("lgW1").textContent = fmt(w1, 3);
      document.getElementById("lgW2").textContent = fmt(w2, 3);
      document.getElementById("lgL").textContent = isFinite(loss) ? fmt(loss, 4) : "--";
      document.getElementById("lgAcc").textContent = isFinite(acc) ? (acc * 100).toFixed(1) + "%" : "--";
    }

    function drawLoss(){
      lctx.clearRect(0, 0, lc.width, lc.height); lctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; lctx.fillRect(0, 0, lc.width, lc.height);
      lctx.fillStyle = "#9aa0aa"; lctx.font = "10px ui-monospace"; lctx.fillText("BCE loss", 8, 14);
      if (lossHist.length < 2) return;
      var mx = 0; for (var i = 0; i < lossHist.length; i++) if (lossHist[i] > mx) mx = lossHist[i];
      if (mx <= 0) mx = 1;
      lctx.strokeStyle = "#a78bfa"; lctx.lineWidth = 2; lctx.beginPath();
      for (var j = 0; j < lossHist.length; j++){
        var x = 8 + j / (lossHist.length - 1) * (lc.width - 16);
        var y = lc.height - 12 - (lossHist[j] / mx) * (lc.height - 26);
        if (j === 0) lctx.moveTo(x, y); else lctx.lineTo(x, y);
      }
      lctx.stroke();
    }

    function loop(){ if (!running) return; for (var s = 0; s < 4; s++) step(); render(); raf = requestAnimationFrame(loop); }

    function seedSample(){
      pts = [];
      var ang = rnd(0, Math.PI), dx = Math.cos(ang) * 0.22, dy = Math.sin(ang) * 0.22;
      for (var i = 0; i < 24; i++) pts.push({ x: clamp(0.5 - dx + gauss() * 0.07, 0.03, 0.97), y: clamp(0.5 - dy + gauss() * 0.07, 0.03, 0.97), c: 0 });
      for (i = 0; i < 24; i++) pts.push({ x: clamp(0.5 + dx + gauss() * 0.07, 0.03, 0.97), y: clamp(0.5 + dy + gauss() * 0.07, 0.03, 0.97), c: 1 });
      reset(); recompute(); render();
    }

    cv.addEventListener("click", function(e){ var p = evtXY(cv, e); pts.push({ x: clamp(p.x / W, 0, 1), y: clamp(p.y / H, 0, 1), c: activeClass }); recompute(); render(); });
    var seg = document.getElementById("lgSeg").querySelectorAll("button");
    for (var s = 0; s < seg.length; s++){
      (function(btn){ btn.addEventListener("click", function(){ for (var z = 0; z < seg.length; z++) seg[z].classList.remove("on"); btn.classList.add("on"); activeClass = parseInt(btn.getAttribute("data-cls"), 10); }); })(seg[s]);
    }
    document.getElementById("lgLr").addEventListener("input", lrFromSlider);
    document.getElementById("lgRun").addEventListener("click", function(){ if (pts.length < 2) return; running = !running; this.textContent = running ? "Pause" : "Train"; if (running) loop(); });
    document.getElementById("lgStep").addEventListener("click", function(){ for (var s2 = 0; s2 < 8; s2++) step(); render(); });
    document.getElementById("lgSeed").addEventListener("click", seedSample);
    document.getElementById("lgClear").addEventListener("click", function(){ pts = []; reset(); render(); });

    lrFromSlider(); reset(); seedSample();
    return { render: render };
  })();

  // ======================================================================
  // 3. k-NN CLASSIFIER  (preserved verbatim)
  // ======================================================================
  var KNN = (function(){
    var cv = document.getElementById("knnCanvas"), ctx = cv.getContext("2d");
    var W = cv.width, H = cv.height;
    var pts = [];          // {x,y,c}
    var activeClass = 0, k = 5;
    var cols = ["#67e8f9", "#fbbf24"];
    var fills = [[103,232,249], [251,191,36]];

    function classifyAt(x, y){
      if (pts.length === 0) return -1;
      // partial selection of k nearest via array of distances
      var ds = [];
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
        var dx = pts[i].x - x, dy = pts[i].y - y;
        ds.push({ d: dx * dx + dy * dy, c: pts[i].c });
      }
      ds.sort(function(a, b){ return a.d - b.d; });
      var kk = Math.min(k, ds.length), v0 = 0, v1 = 0;
      for (var j = 0; j < kk; j++){ if (ds[j].c === 0) v0++; else v1++; }
      return v0 === v1 ? (ds[0].c) : (v0 > v1 ? 0 : 1);
    }
    function render(){
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H); ctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
      var cell = 10;
      if (pts.length > 0){
        var img = ctx.createImageData(W, H);
        for (var gy = 0; gy < H; gy += cell){
          for (var gx = 0; gx < W; gx += cell){
            var c = classifyAt(gx + cell / 2, gy + cell / 2);
            var rgb = c < 0 ? [20, 22, 30] : fills[c];
            for (var yy = gy; yy < gy + cell && yy < H; yy++){
              for (var xx = gx; xx < gx + cell && xx < W; xx++){
                var idx = (yy * W + xx) * 4;
                img.data[idx] = rgb[0]; img.data[idx + 1] = rgb[1]; img.data[idx + 2] = rgb[2]; img.data[idx + 3] = c < 0 ? 255 : 46;
              }
            }
          }
        }
        ctx.putImageData(img, 0, 0);
      }
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
        ctx.fillStyle = cols[pts[i].c]; ctx.strokeStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(pts[i].x, pts[i].y, 5, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
      }
      var a = 0, b = 0; for (var p = 0; p < pts.length; p++){ if (pts[p].c === 0) a++; else b++; }
      document.getElementById("knnA").textContent = a;
      document.getElementById("knnB").textContent = b;
    }
    function seedSample(){
      pts = [];
      var i;
      for (i = 0; i < 22; i++) pts.push({ x: clamp(rnd(0.15, 0.45) * W + gauss() * 30, 6, W - 6), y: clamp(rnd(0.2, 0.7) * H + gauss() * 30, 6, H - 6), c: 0 });
      for (i = 0; i < 22; i++) pts.push({ x: clamp(rnd(0.55, 0.85) * W + gauss() * 30, 6, W - 6), y: clamp(rnd(0.3, 0.8) * H + gauss() * 30, 6, H - 6), c: 1 });
      render();
    }
    cv.addEventListener("click", function(e){ var p = evtXY(cv, e); pts.push({ x: p.x, y: p.y, c: activeClass }); render(); });
    var seg = document.getElementById("knnSeg").querySelectorAll("button");
    for (var s = 0; s < seg.length; s++){
      (function(btn){ btn.addEventListener("click", function(){ for (var z = 0; z < seg.length; z++) seg[z].classList.remove("on"); btn.classList.add("on"); activeClass = parseInt(btn.getAttribute("data-cls"), 10); }); })(seg[s]);
    }
    document.getElementById("knnK").addEventListener("input", function(){ k = parseInt(this.value, 10); document.getElementById("knnKV").textContent = k; render(); });
    document.getElementById("knnSeed").addEventListener("click", seedSample);
    document.getElementById("knnClear").addEventListener("click", function(){ pts = []; render(); });

    seedSample();
    return { render: render };
  })();

  // ======================================================================
  // 4. K-MEANS (Lloyd's algorithm)  (preserved verbatim)
  // ======================================================================
  var KM = (function(){
    var cv = document.getElementById("kmCanvas"), ctx = cv.getContext("2d");
    var W = cv.width, H = cv.height;
    var palette = ["#67e8f9", "#a78bfa", "#fbbf24", "#86efac", "#fca5a5", "#f0abfc"];
    var pts = [], cents = [], assign = [], K = 3, N = 220;
    var iter = 0, inertia = NaN, moved = NaN, running = false, raf = null, converged = false;

    function seed(){
      pts = []; iter = 0; inertia = NaN; converged = false;
      var blobs = 2 + ((Math.random() * 4) | 0);
      var centers = [];
      for (var b = 0; b < blobs; b++) centers.push({ x: rnd(0.12, 0.88) * W, y: rnd(0.12, 0.88) * H });
      for (var i = 0; i < N; i++){
        var c = centers[(Math.random() * blobs) | 0];
        var spread = Math.min(W, H) * 0.07;
        pts.push({ x: clamp(c.x + gauss() * spread, 4, W - 4), y: clamp(c.y + gauss() * spread, 4, H - 4) });
      }
      initCents();
    }
    function initCents(){
      // k-means++ style: first random, rest by distance weighting
      cents = []; assign = [];
      cents.push({ x: pts[(Math.random() * pts.length) | 0].x, y: pts[(Math.random() * pts.length) | 0].y });
      while (cents.length < K){
        var d2 = [], sum = 0, i, j;
        for (i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
          var best = Infinity;
          for (j = 0; j < cents.length; j++){
            var dx = pts[i].x - cents[j].x, dy = pts[i].y - cents[j].y, d = dx * dx + dy * dy;
            if (d < best) best = d;
          }
          d2.push(best); sum += best;
        }
        var r = Math.random() * sum, acc = 0, pick = 0;
        for (i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){ acc += d2[i]; if (acc >= r){ pick = i; break; } }
        cents.push({ x: pts[pick].x, y: pts[pick].y });
      }
      assignAll(); iter = 0; converged = false;
    }
    function assignAll(){
      inertia = 0;
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
        var best = Infinity, bi = 0;
        for (var c = 0; c < cents.length; c++){
          var dx = pts[i].x - cents[c].x, dy = pts[i].y - cents[c].y, d = dx * dx + dy * dy;
          if (d < best){ best = d; bi = c; }
        }
        assign[i] = bi; inertia += best;
      }
    }
    function step(){
      if (converged) return;
      // recompute centroids = mean of assigned points
      var sumx = [], sumy = [], cnt = [], c;
      for (c = 0; c < K; c++){ sumx[c] = 0; sumy[c] = 0; cnt[c] = 0; }
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){ var a = assign[i]; sumx[a] += pts[i].x; sumy[a] += pts[i].y; cnt[a]++; }
      moved = 0;
      for (c = 0; c < K; c++){
        if (cnt[c] === 0){ continue; }
        var nx = sumx[c] / cnt[c], ny = sumy[c] / cnt[c];
        moved += Math.sqrt((nx - cents[c].x) * (nx - cents[c].x) + (ny - cents[c].y) * (ny - cents[c].y));
        cents[c].x = nx; cents[c].y = ny;
      }
      assignAll();
      iter++;
      if (moved < 0.4){ converged = true; }
    }
    function draw(){
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H); ctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
        ctx.fillStyle = palette[assign[i] % palette.length];
        ctx.globalAlpha = 0.85;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(pts[i].x, pts[i].y, 3.2, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill();
      }
      ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
      for (var c = 0; c < cents.length; c++){
        ctx.strokeStyle = "#e8e8ee"; ctx.lineWidth = 3;
        var s = 9, cx = cents[c].x, cy = cents[c].y;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(cx - s, cy); ctx.lineTo(cx + s, cy); ctx.moveTo(cx, cy - s); ctx.lineTo(cx, cy + s); ctx.stroke();
        ctx.strokeStyle = palette[c % palette.length]; ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(cx, cy, 12, 0, 6.2832); ctx.stroke();
      }
      document.getElementById("kmIt").textContent = iter;
      document.getElementById("kmIn").textContent = isFinite(inertia) ? (inertia / 1000).toFixed(1) + "k" : "--";
      document.getElementById("kmMv").textContent = isFinite(moved) ? fmt(moved, 1) : "--";
      document.getElementById("kmSt").textContent = converged ? "converged" : (running ? "running" : "ready");
    }
    function loop(){ if (!running) return; step(); draw(); if (converged){ running = false; document.getElementById("kmRun").textContent = "Run Lloyd"; return; } raf = requestAnimationFrame(function(){ setTimeout(loop, 260); }); }

    document.getElementById("kmK").addEventListener("input", function(){ K = parseInt(this.value, 10); document.getElementById("kmKV").textContent = K; initCents(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("kmN").addEventListener("input", function(){ N = parseInt(this.value, 10); document.getElementById("kmNV").textContent = N; seed(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("kmRun").addEventListener("click", function(){ if (converged) initCents(); running = !running; this.textContent = running ? "Pause" : "Run Lloyd"; if (running) loop(); });
    document.getElementById("kmStep").addEventListener("click", function(){ step(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("kmReseed").addEventListener("click", function(){ seed(); draw(); });

    seed(); draw();
    return { draw: draw };
  })();

  // ======================================================================
  // 5. DECISION TREE (NEW): recursive Gini/entropy splits on 2D points
  // ======================================================================
  var TREE = (function(){
    var cv = document.getElementById("trCanvas"), ctx = cv.getContext("2d");
    var W = cv.width, H = cv.height;
    var pts = [];            // {x:0..1, y:0..1, c:0|1}
    var activeClass = 0, criterion = "gini", maxDepth = 3;
    var root = null, leafCount = 0, depthUsed = 0;
    var cols = ["#67e8f9", "#fbbf24"];
    var fills = [[103,232,249], [251,191,36]];

    function impurity(subset){
      var n = subset.length; if (n === 0) return 0;
      var n1 = 0; for (var i = 0; i < n; i++) if (subset[i].c === 1) n1++;
      var p1 = n1 / n, p0 = 1 - p1;
      if (criterion === "gini") return 1 - p0 * p0 - p1 * p1;
      // entropy (log2)
      var h = 0;
      if (p0 > 0) h -= p0 * Math.log(p0) / Math.log(2);
      if (p1 > 0) h -= p1 * Math.log(p1) / Math.log(2);
      return h;
    }
    function majority(subset){
      var n1 = 0; for (var i = 0; i < subset.length; i++) if (subset[i].c === 1) n1++;
      return n1 * 2 >= subset.length ? 1 : 0;
    }
    function bestSplit(subset){
      var parentI = impurity(subset), n = subset.length;
      var best = null, bestGain = 1e-9;
      for (var feat = 0; feat < 2; feat++){
        // candidate thresholds = midpoints of sorted unique values
        var vals = [];
        for (var i = 0; i < n; i++) vals.push(feat === 0 ? subset[i].x : subset[i].y);
        vals.sort(function(a, b){ return a - b; });
        for (var t = 0; t < n - 1; t++){
          if (vals[t] === vals[t + 1]) continue;
          var thr = (vals[t] + vals[t + 1]) / 2;
          var L = [], R = [];
          for (i = 0; i < n; i++){
            var v = feat === 0 ? subset[i].x : subset[i].y;
            if (v <= thr) L.push(subset[i]); else R.push(subset[i]);
          }
          if (L.length === 0 || R.length === 0) continue;
          var gain = parentI - (L.length / n) * impurity(L) - (R.length / n) * impurity(R);
          if (gain > bestGain){ bestGain = gain; best = { feat: feat, thr: thr, L: L, R: R }; }
        }
      }
      return best;
    }
    function buildNode(subset, depth){
      var node = { leaf: true, cls: majority(subset), count: subset.length, depth: depth };
      if (depth >= depthUsed) depthUsed = depth;
      if (depth >= maxDepth || subset.length < 2 || impurity(subset) < 1e-9){ leafCount++; return node; }
      var sp = bestSplit(subset);
      if (!sp){ leafCount++; return node; }
      node.leaf = false; node.feat = sp.feat; node.thr = sp.thr;
      node.L = buildNode(sp.L, depth + 1);
      node.R = buildNode(sp.R, depth + 1);
      return node;
    }
    function predict(node, x, y){
      while (!node.leaf){
        var v = node.feat === 0 ? x : y;
        node = (v <= node.thr) ? node.L : node.R;
      }
      return node.cls;
    }
    function build(){
      if (pts.length < 2){ root = null; render(); return; }
      root = null; leafCount = 0; depthUsed = 0;
      root = buildNode(pts.slice(), 0);
      render();
    }
    function accuracy(){
      if (!root || pts.length === 0) return NaN;
      var correct = 0;
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++) if (predict(root, pts[i].x, pts[i].y) === pts[i].c) correct++;
      return correct / pts.length;
    }
    // recursively paint a region [x0,x1]x[y0,y1] in normalised coords
    function paintNode(node, x0, x1, y0, y1){
      if (node.leaf){
        var rgb = fills[node.cls];
        ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(" + rgb[0] + "," + rgb[1] + "," + rgb[2] + ",0.20)";
        ctx.fillRect(x0 * W, y0 * H, (x1 - x0) * W, (y1 - y0) * H);
        return;
      }
      if (node.feat === 0){
        paintNode(node.L, x0, node.thr, y0, y1);
        paintNode(node.R, node.thr, x1, y0, y1);
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(255,255,255,0.55)"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(node.thr * W, y0 * H); ctx.lineTo(node.thr * W, y1 * H); ctx.stroke();
      } else {
        paintNode(node.L, x0, x1, y0, node.thr);
        paintNode(node.R, x0, x1, node.thr, y1);
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(255,255,255,0.55)"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x0 * W, node.thr * H); ctx.lineTo(x1 * W, node.thr * H); ctx.stroke();
      }
    }
    function render(){
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H); ctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
      if (root) paintNode(root, 0, 1, 0, 1);
      for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
        ctx.fillStyle = cols[pts[i].c]; ctx.strokeStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.4;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(pts[i].x * W, pts[i].y * H, 5, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
      }
      document.getElementById("trLeaves").textContent = root ? leafCount : "--";
      document.getElementById("trUsed").textContent = root ? depthUsed : "--";
      var ac = accuracy();
      document.getElementById("trAcc").textContent = isFinite(ac) ? (ac * 100).toFixed(1) + "%" : "--";
      document.getElementById("trN").textContent = pts.length;
    }
    function seedSample(){
      pts = [];
      // XOR-like four blobs: diagonal pairs share a class
      var centers = [ {x:0.28,y:0.28,c:0}, {x:0.72,y:0.72,c:0}, {x:0.72,y:0.28,c:1}, {x:0.28,y:0.72,c:1} ];
      for (var b = 0; b < centers.length; b++){
        for (var i = 0; i < 16; i++){
          pts.push({ x: clamp(centers[b].x + gauss() * 0.08, 0.02, 0.98), y: clamp(centers[b].y + gauss() * 0.08, 0.02, 0.98), c: centers[b].c });
        }
      }
      root = null; render();
    }
    cv.addEventListener("click", function(e){ var p = evtXY(cv, e); pts.push({ x: clamp(p.x / W, 0, 1), y: clamp(p.y / H, 0, 1), c: activeClass }); root = null; render(); });
    var seg = document.getElementById("trSeg").querySelectorAll("button");
    for (var s = 0; s < seg.length; s++){
      (function(btn){ btn.addEventListener("click", function(){ for (var z = 0; z < seg.length; z++) seg[z].classList.remove("on"); btn.classList.add("on"); activeClass = parseInt(btn.getAttribute("data-cls"), 10); }); })(seg[s]);
    }
    var cseg = document.getElementById("trCrit").querySelectorAll("button");
    for (var cs = 0; cs < cseg.length; cs++){
      (function(btn){ btn.addEventListener("click", function(){ for (var z = 0; z < cseg.length; z++) cseg[z].classList.remove("on"); btn.classList.add("on"); criterion = btn.getAttribute("data-crit"); }); })(cseg[cs]);
    }
    document.getElementById("trDepth").addEventListener("input", function(){ maxDepth = parseInt(this.value, 10); document.getElementById("trDepthV").textContent = maxDepth; });
    document.getElementById("trBuild").addEventListener("click", build);
    document.getElementById("trSeed").addEventListener("click", seedSample);
    document.getElementById("trClear").addEventListener("click", function(){ pts = []; root = null; render(); });

    seedSample();
    return { render: render };
  })();

  // ======================================================================
  // 6. PCA (NEW): covariance + power iteration -> principal axes
  // ======================================================================
  var PCA = (function(){
    var cv = document.getElementById("pcaCanvas"), ctx = cv.getContext("2d");
    var W = cv.width, H = cv.height;
    var pts = [];            // {x:0..1, y:0..1}
    var mean = null, v1 = null, v2 = null, l1 = NaN, l2 = NaN, iters = 0, showProj = true;

    function compute(){
      var n = pts.length;
      if (n < 2){ mean = null; v1 = null; v2 = null; l1 = NaN; l2 = NaN; iters = 0; return; }
      // center
      var mx = 0, my = 0, i;
      for (i = 0; i < n; i++){ mx += pts[i].x; my += pts[i].y; }
      mx /= n; my /= n; mean = { x: mx, y: my };
      // 2x2 covariance
      var cxx = 0, cxy = 0, cyy = 0;
      for (i = 0; i < n; i++){ var dx = pts[i].x - mx, dy = pts[i].y - my; cxx += dx * dx; cxy += dx * dy; cyy += dy * dy; }
      cxx /= n; cxy /= n; cyy /= n;
      // power iteration for top eigenvector
      var vx = rnd(-1, 1), vy = rnd(-1, 1), nrm = Math.sqrt(vx * vx + vy * vy) || 1; vx /= nrm; vy /= nrm;
      iters = 0; var prevx = 0, prevy = 0;
      for (var it = 0; it < 200; it++){
        var nx = cxx * vx + cxy * vy;
        var ny = cxy * vx + cyy * vy;
        var m = Math.sqrt(nx * nx + ny * ny);
        if (m < 1e-12) break;
        nx /= m; ny /= m;
        iters++;
        // fix sign for stability
        if (nx * vx + ny * vy < 0){ nx = -nx; ny = -ny; }
        if (Math.abs(nx - vx) < 1e-9 && Math.abs(ny - vy) < 1e-9){ vx = nx; vy = ny; break; }
        vx = nx; vy = ny;
      }
      // Rayleigh quotient = top eigenvalue
      l1 = vx * (cxx * vx + cxy * vy) + vy * (cxy * vx + cyy * vy);
      // second eigenvector orthogonal in 2D; eigenvalue via trace
      v1 = { x: vx, y: vy };
      v2 = { x: -vy, y: vx };
      l2 = (cxx + cyy) - l1;
      if (l2 < 0) l2 = 0;
    }

    function arrow(cx, cy, dx, dy, len, color){
      var ex = cx + dx * len, ey = cy + dy * len;
      ctx.strokeStyle = color; ctx.fillStyle = color; ctx.lineWidth = 2.5;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(cx, cy); ctx.lineTo(ex, ey); ctx.stroke();
      // head
      var ang = Math.atan2(ey - cy, ex - cx), s = 9;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(ex, ey);
      ctx.lineTo(ex - s * Math.cos(ang - 0.4), ey - s * Math.sin(ang - 0.4));
      ctx.lineTo(ex - s * Math.cos(ang + 0.4), ey - s * Math.sin(ang + 0.4));
      ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
    }
    function draw(){
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H); ctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
      // faint grid
      ctx.strokeStyle = "#15171f"; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      for (var g = 1; g < 10; g++){ ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(g / 10 * W, 0); ctx.lineTo(g / 10 * W, H); ctx.stroke(); ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(0, g / 10 * H); ctx.lineTo(W, g / 10 * H); ctx.stroke(); }
      // projections onto PC1
      if (mean && v1 && showProj){
        var cx = mean.x * W, cy = mean.y * H;
        var ax = v1.x * W, ay = v1.y * H, alen = Math.sqrt(ax * ax + ay * ay) || 1;
        var ux = ax / alen, uy = ay / alen; // unit direction in pixels
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(251,191,36,0.4)"; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++){
          var pxp = pts[i].x * W, pyp = pts[i].y * H;
          var t = (pxp - cx) * ux + (pyp - cy) * uy;
          var projx = cx + t * ux, projy = cy + t * uy;
          ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(pxp, pyp); ctx.lineTo(projx, projy); ctx.stroke();
          ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(251,191,36,0.8)";
          ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(projx, projy, 2.4, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill();
        }
      }
      // points
      for (var p = 0; p < pts.length; p++){
        ctx.fillStyle = "#e8e8ee"; ctx.strokeStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(pts[p].x * W, pts[p].y * H, 4, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
      }
      // axes
      if (mean && v1){
        var ccx = mean.x * W, ccy = mean.y * H;
        var sc1 = 60 + Math.sqrt(Math.max(l1, 0)) * 900;
        var sc2 = 40 + Math.sqrt(Math.max(l2, 0)) * 900;
        // draw both directions of PC1
        arrow(ccx, ccy, v1.x, v1.y, sc1, "#67e8f9");
        arrow(ccx, ccy, -v1.x, -v1.y, sc1, "#67e8f9");
        arrow(ccx, ccy, v2.x, v2.y, sc2, "#a78bfa");
        arrow(ccx, ccy, -v2.x, -v2.y, sc2, "#a78bfa");
        ctx.fillStyle = "#86efac"; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(ccx, ccy, 4, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill();
      }
      var tot = (l1 + l2);
      document.getElementById("pcaL1").textContent = isFinite(l1) ? (l1 * 1000).toFixed(2) : "--";
      document.getElementById("pcaL2").textContent = isFinite(l2) ? (l2 * 1000).toFixed(2) : "--";
      document.getElementById("pcaExp").textContent = (isFinite(l1) && tot > 0) ? (l1 / tot * 100).toFixed(1) + "%" : "--";
      document.getElementById("pcaIt").textContent = iters || "--";
      document.getElementById("pcaAng").textContent = v1 ? (Math.atan2(v1.y, v1.x) * 180 / Math.PI).toFixed(1) + " deg" : "--";
    }
    function seedSample(){
      pts = [];
      var ang = rnd(0.3, 1.2), ca = Math.cos(ang), sa = Math.sin(ang);
      for (var i = 0; i < 50; i++){
        var a = gauss() * 0.24, b = gauss() * 0.06; // elongated cloud
        var x = 0.5 + a * ca - b * sa;
        var y = 0.5 + a * sa + b * ca;
        pts.push({ x: clamp(x, 0.03, 0.97), y: clamp(y, 0.03, 0.97) });
      }
      compute(); draw();
    }
    cv.addEventListener("click", function(e){ var p = evtXY(cv, e); pts.push({ x: clamp(p.x / W, 0, 1), y: clamp(p.y / H, 0, 1) }); compute(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("pcaRun").addEventListener("click", function(){ compute(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("pcaSeed").addEventListener("click", seedSample);
    document.getElementById("pcaClear").addEventListener("click", function(){ pts = []; mean = null; v1 = null; v2 = null; l1 = NaN; l2 = NaN; iters = 0; draw(); });
    document.getElementById("pcaProj").addEventListener("click", function(){ showProj = !showProj; draw(); });

    seedSample();
    return { draw: draw };
  })();

  // ======================================================================
  // 7. NEURAL NETWORK (real backprop): 2 -> 8 -> 8 -> 1  (preserved verbatim)
  // ======================================================================
  var NN = (function(){
    var cv = document.getElementById("nnCanvas"), ctx = cv.getContext("2d");
    var lc = document.getElementById("nnLoss"), lctx = lc.getContext("2d");
    var W = cv.width, H = cv.height;
    var sizes = [2, 8, 8, 1];
    var Wm = [], Bm = [];   // weights[layer][j][i], biases[layer][j]
    var data = [], dataset = "xor";
    var epoch = 0, loss = NaN, acc = NaN, lossHist = [], running = false, raf = null, lr = 0.2;

    function tanh(x){ if (x > 20) return 1; if (x < -20) return -1; var e = Math.exp(2 * x); return (e - 1) / (e + 1); }
    function sigmoid(x){ if (x < -30) return 0; if (x > 30) return 1; return 1 / (1 + Math.exp(-x)); }

    function initNet(){
      Wm = []; Bm = [];
      for (var l = 1; l < sizes.length; l++){
        var nIn = sizes[l - 1], nOut = sizes[l];
        var limit = Math.sqrt(6 / (nIn + nOut)); // Xavier
        var wl = [], bl = [];
        for (var j = 0; j < nOut; j++){
          var row = [];
          for (var i = 0; i < nIn; i++) row.push(rnd(-limit, limit));
          wl.push(row); bl.push(0);
        }
        Wm.push(wl); Bm.push(bl);
      }
      epoch = 0; loss = NaN; acc = NaN; lossHist = [];
    }

    // forward pass; returns activations per layer (a[0] = input)
    function forward(input){
      var a = [input], cur = input;
      for (var l = 0; l < Wm.length; l++){
        var next = [], isLast = (l === Wm.length - 1);
        for (var j = 0; j < Wm[l].length; j++){
          var z = Bm[l][j];
          for (var i = 0; i < cur.length; i++) z += Wm[l][j][i] * cur[i];
          next.push(isLast ? sigmoid(z) : tanh(z));
        }
        a.push(next); cur = next;
      }
      return a;
    }

    function trainEpoch(){
      // accumulate gradients over full batch
      var gW = [], gB = [], l, j, i;
      for (l = 0; l < Wm.length; l++){
        gW[l] = []; gB[l] = [];
        for (j = 0; j < Wm[l].length; j++){ gW[l][j] = []; for (i = 0; i < Wm[l][j].length; i++) gW[l][j][i] = 0; gB[l][j] = 0; }
      }
      var totalLoss = 0, correct = 0, n = data.length;
      for (var s = 0; s < n; s++){
        var x = [data[s].x, data[s].y], target = data[s].c;
        var a = forward(x);
        var out = a[a.length - 1][0];
        var oc = clamp(out, 1e-7, 1 - 1e-7);
        totalLoss += -(target * Math.log(oc) + (1 - target) * Math.log(1 - oc));
        if ((out > 0.5 ? 1 : 0) === target) correct++;

        // backprop: delta for each layer
        var deltas = [];
        for (l = 0; l < Wm.length; l++) deltas[l] = [];
        // output layer (sigmoid + BCE): dL/dz = out - target
        var L = Wm.length - 1;
        deltas[L][0] = out - target;
        // hidden layers (tanh): delta = (W^T delta_next) * (1 - a^2)
        for (l = L - 1; l >= 0; l--){
          var aOut = a[l + 1];
          for (j = 0; j < Wm[l].length; j++){
            var sum = 0;
            for (var jn = 0; jn < Wm[l + 1].length; jn++) sum += Wm[l + 1][jn][j] * deltas[l + 1][jn];
            deltas[l][j] = sum * (1 - aOut[j] * aOut[j]);
          }
        }
        // accumulate gradients
        for (l = 0; l < Wm.length; l++){
          var aPrev = a[l];
          for (j = 0; j < Wm[l].length; j++){
            for (i = 0; i < aPrev.length; i++) gW[l][j][i] += deltas[l][j] * aPrev[i];
            gB[l][j] += deltas[l][j];
          }
        }
      }
      // apply averaged gradients
      for (l = 0; l < Wm.length; l++){
        for (j = 0; j < Wm[l].length; j++){
          for (i = 0; i < Wm[l][j].length; i++) Wm[l][j][i] -= lr * gW[l][j][i] / n;
          Bm[l][j] -= lr * gB[l][j] / n;
        }
      }
      epoch++;
      loss = totalLoss / n;
      acc = correct / n;
      lossHist.push(loss); if (lossHist.length > 700) lossHist.shift();
    }

    function genData(){
      data = []; var i, n;
      if (dataset === "xor"){
        n = 200;
        for (i = 0; i < n; i++){
          var qx = Math.random() < 0.5 ? rnd(0.05, 0.45) : rnd(0.55, 0.95);
          var qy = Math.random() < 0.5 ? rnd(0.05, 0.45) : rnd(0.55, 0.95);
          var c = ((qx > 0.5) !== (qy > 0.5)) ? 1 : 0;
          data.push({ x: qx, y: qy, c: c });
        }
      } else if (dataset === "circles"){
        n = 220;
        for (i = 0; i < n; i++){
          var inner = i < n / 2;
          var rad = inner ? rnd(0, 0.22) : rnd(0.34, 0.48);
          var th = rnd(0, 6.2832);
          data.push({ x: 0.5 + rad * Math.cos(th), y: 0.5 + rad * Math.sin(th), c: inner ? 1 : 0 });
        }
      } else if (dataset === "moons"){
        n = 220;
        for (i = 0; i < n; i++){
          if (i < n / 2){ var t1 = rnd(0, Math.PI); data.push({ x: 0.32 + 0.32 * Math.cos(t1) + gauss() * 0.025, y: 0.62 - 0.30 * Math.sin(t1) + gauss() * 0.025, c: 0 }); }
          else { var t2 = rnd(0, Math.PI); data.push({ x: 0.68 - 0.32 * Math.cos(t2) + gauss() * 0.025, y: 0.40 + 0.30 * Math.sin(t2) + gauss() * 0.025, c: 1 }); }
        }
      } else { // spiral
        n = 240;
        for (i = 0; i < n / 2; i++){
          var r = i / (n / 2) * 0.46;
          var t = i / (n / 2) * 4 + gauss() * 0.12;
          data.push({ x: 0.5 + r * Math.cos(t), y: 0.5 + r * Math.sin(t), c: 0 });
          data.push({ x: 0.5 + r * Math.cos(t + Math.PI), y: 0.5 + r * Math.sin(t + Math.PI), c: 1 });
        }
      }
      for (i = 0; i < data.length; i++){ data[i].x = clamp(data[i].x, 0, 1); data[i].y = clamp(data[i].y, 0, 1); }
    }

    function draw(){
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H); ctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
      // prediction surface on coarse grid
      var cell = 8;
      var img = ctx.createImageData(W, H);
      for (var gy = 0; gy < H; gy += cell){
        for (var gx = 0; gx < W; gx += cell){
          var nx = (gx + cell / 2) / W, ny = (gy + cell / 2) / H;
          var a = forward([nx, ny]);
          var p = a[a.length - 1][0]; // 0..1
          // class1 = amber, class0 = cyan ; intensity by confidence
          var t = clamp((p - 0.5) * 2, -1, 1);
          var rr, gg, bb;
          if (t >= 0){ rr = 80 + t * 171; gg = 60 + t * 131; bb = 30; }   // toward amber
          else { var u = -t; rr = 40; gg = 60 + u * 172; bb = 60 + u * 189; } // toward cyan
          for (var yy = gy; yy < gy + cell && yy < H; yy++){
            for (var xx = gx; xx < gx + cell && xx < W; xx++){
              var idx = (yy * W + xx) * 4;
              img.data[idx] = rr; img.data[idx + 1] = gg; img.data[idx + 2] = bb; img.data[idx + 3] = 70;
            }
          }
        }
      }
      ctx.putImageData(img, 0, 0);
      // data points
      for (var s = 0; s < data.length; s++){
        ctx.fillStyle = data[s].c === 1 ? "#fbbf24" : "#67e8f9";
        ctx.strokeStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(data[s].x * W, data[s].y * H, 4, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
      }
      drawLoss();
      document.getElementById("nnE").textContent = epoch;
      document.getElementById("nnL").textContent = isFinite(loss) ? fmt(loss, 4) : "--";
      document.getElementById("nnAcc").textContent = isFinite(acc) ? (acc * 100).toFixed(1) + "%" : "--";
      document.getElementById("nnSt").textContent = running ? "training" : (epoch ? "paused" : "idle");
    }
    function drawLoss(){
      lctx.clearRect(0, 0, lc.width, lc.height); lctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; lctx.fillRect(0, 0, lc.width, lc.height);
      lctx.fillStyle = "#9aa0aa"; lctx.font = "10px ui-monospace"; lctx.fillText("BCE loss", 8, 14);
      if (lossHist.length < 2) return;
      var mx = 0; for (var i = 0; i < lossHist.length; i++) if (lossHist[i] > mx) mx = lossHist[i];
      if (mx <= 0) mx = 1;
      lctx.strokeStyle = "#a78bfa"; lctx.lineWidth = 2; lctx.beginPath();
      for (var j = 0; j < lossHist.length; j++){
        var x = 8 + j / (lossHist.length - 1) * (lc.width - 16);
        var y = lc.height - 12 - (lossHist[j] / mx) * (lc.height - 30);
        if (j === 0) lctx.moveTo(x, y); else lctx.lineTo(x, y);
      }
      lctx.stroke();
    }
    function loop(){ if (!running) return; for (var s = 0; s < 4; s++) trainEpoch(); draw(); raf = requestAnimationFrame(loop); }

    document.getElementById("nnData").addEventListener("change", function(){ dataset = this.value; initNet(); genData(); running = false; document.getElementById("nnRun").textContent = "Train"; draw(); });
    document.getElementById("nnLr").addEventListener("input", function(){ lr = Math.pow(10, parseFloat(this.value)); document.getElementById("nnLrV").textContent = fmt(lr, lr < 0.01 ? 4 : 2); });
    document.getElementById("nnRun").addEventListener("click", function(){ running = !running; this.textContent = running ? "Pause" : "Train"; if (running) loop(); });
    document.getElementById("nnReset").addEventListener("click", function(){ running = false; document.getElementById("nnRun").textContent = "Train"; initNet(); draw(); });

    lr = Math.pow(10, parseFloat(document.getElementById("nnLr").value));
    document.getElementById("nnLrV").textContent = fmt(lr, 2);
    initNet(); genData(); draw();
    return { draw: draw };
  })();

  // ======================================================================
  // 8. OPTIMIZERS COMPARED (NEW): SGD vs momentum vs Adam on a 2D surface
  // ======================================================================
  var OPT = (function(){
    var cv = document.getElementById("optCanvas"), ctx = cv.getContext("2d");
    var lc = document.getElementById("optLoss"), lctx = lc.getContext("2d");
    var W = cv.width, H = cv.height;
    var surface = "bowl", lr = 0.04, iter = 0, running = false, raf = null;
    var start = { x: -2.2, y: 2.2 };   // domain coords
    // domain box in math coords
    var X0 = -3, X1 = 3, Y0 = -3, Y1 = 3;
    var opts = null;                    // three optimizer states
    var paths = { sgd: [], mom: [], adam: [] };
    var hist = { sgd: [], mom: [], adam: [] };
    var colors = { sgd: "#67e8f9", mom: "#fbbf24", adam: "#a78bfa" };

    // loss + analytic gradient for each surface
    function fval(x, y){
      if (surface === "bowl") return 0.5 * (0.15 * x * x + 2.2 * y * y);
      if (surface === "saddle") return 0.5 * (x * x - y * y) + 0.05 * y * y * y * y + 0.3 * y * y;
      // rosenbrock (scaled down)
      var a = 1, b = 12;
      return ((a - x) * (a - x) + b * (y - x * x) * (y - x * x)) / 12;
    }
    function grad(x, y){
      if (surface === "bowl") return { gx: 0.15 * x, gy: 2.2 * y };
      if (surface === "saddle") return { gx: x, gy: -y + 0.2 * y * y * y + 0.6 * y };
      var a = 1, b = 12;
      var gx = (-2 * (a - x) - 4 * b * x * (y - x * x)) / 12;
      var gy = (2 * b * (y - x * x)) / 12;
      return { gx: gx, gy: gy };
    }
    function minPoint(){
      if (surface === "rosen") return { x: 1, y: 1 };
      return { x: 0, y: 0 };
    }

    function toPx(x, y){ return { x: (x - X0) / (X1 - X0) * W, y: (1 - (y - Y0) / (Y1 - Y0)) * H }; }
    function toMath(px, py){ return { x: X0 + px / W * (X1 - X0), y: Y0 + (1 - py / H) * (Y1 - Y0) }; }

    function reset(){
      iter = 0;
      paths = { sgd: [{ x: start.x, y: start.y }], mom: [{ x: start.x, y: start.y }], adam: [{ x: start.x, y: start.y }] };
      hist = { sgd: [], mom: [], adam: [] };
      opts = {
        sgd:  { x: start.x, y: start.y },
        mom:  { x: start.x, y: start.y, vx: 0, vy: 0, beta: 0.9 },
        adam: { x: start.x, y: start.y, mx: 0, my: 0, sx: 0, sy: 0, b1: 0.9, b2: 0.999, t: 0 }
      };
    }

    function step(){
      // SGD
      var s = opts.sgd, g = grad(s.x, s.y);
      s.x -= lr * g.gx; s.y -= lr * g.gy;
      paths.sgd.push({ x: s.x, y: s.y });
      // Momentum
      var m = opts.mom, gm = grad(m.x, m.y);
      m.vx = m.beta * m.vx + gm.gx; m.vy = m.beta * m.vy + gm.gy;
      m.x -= lr * m.vx; m.y -= lr * m.vy;
      paths.mom.push({ x: m.x, y: m.y });
      // Adam
      var ad = opts.adam, ga = grad(ad.x, ad.y);
      ad.t++;
      ad.mx = ad.b1 * ad.mx + (1 - ad.b1) * ga.gx; ad.my = ad.b1 * ad.my + (1 - ad.b1) * ga.gy;
      ad.sx = ad.b2 * ad.sx + (1 - ad.b2) * ga.gx * ga.gx; ad.sy = ad.b2 * ad.sy + (1 - ad.b2) * ga.gy * ga.gy;
      var mhx = ad.mx / (1 - Math.pow(ad.b1, ad.t)), mhy = ad.my / (1 - Math.pow(ad.b1, ad.t));
      var shx = ad.sx / (1 - Math.pow(ad.b2, ad.t)), shy = ad.sy / (1 - Math.pow(ad.b2, ad.t));
      var adamLr = lr * 8; // Adam's effective step is smaller; scale for comparability
      ad.x -= adamLr * mhx / (Math.sqrt(shx) + 1e-8); ad.y -= adamLr * mhy / (Math.sqrt(shy) + 1e-8);
      paths.adam.push({ x: ad.x, y: ad.y });

      hist.sgd.push(fval(s.x, s.y));
      hist.mom.push(fval(m.x, m.y));
      hist.adam.push(fval(ad.x, ad.y));
      if (hist.sgd.length > 400){ hist.sgd.shift(); hist.mom.shift(); hist.adam.shift(); }
      iter++;
    }

    function draw(){
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H); ctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
      // contour shading via per-cell loss value
      var cell = 8, img = ctx.createImageData(W, H), maxv = 0;
      // estimate a normalisation by sampling corners + center
      var samples = [fval(X0, Y0), fval(X1, Y1), fval(X0, Y1), fval(X1, Y0), fval(0, 0)];
      for (var si = 0; si < samples.length; si++) if (samples[si] > maxv) maxv = samples[si];
      if (maxv <= 0) maxv = 1;
      for (var gy = 0; gy < H; gy += cell){
        for (var gx = 0; gx < W; gx += cell){
          var mc = toMath(gx + cell / 2, gy + cell / 2);
          var v = fval(mc.x, mc.y);
          var t = clamp(v / maxv, 0, 1);
          // dark (low loss) -> bright steel (high loss)
          var rr = 10 + t * 40, gg = 12 + t * 44, bb = 18 + t * 70;
          // contour bands
          var band = (Math.floor(Math.sqrt(t) * 9) % 2 === 0) ? 0 : 14;
          rr += band; gg += band; bb += band;
          for (var yy = gy; yy < gy + cell && yy < H; yy++){
            for (var xx = gx; xx < gx + cell && xx < W; xx++){
              var idx = (yy * W + xx) * 4;
              img.data[idx] = rr; img.data[idx + 1] = gg; img.data[idx + 2] = bb; img.data[idx + 3] = 255;
            }
          }
        }
      }
      ctx.putImageData(img, 0, 0);
      // minimum marker
      var mp = minPoint(), mpx = toPx(mp.x, mp.y);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "#86efac"; ctx.lineWidth = 2;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(mpx.x, mpx.y, 8, 0, 6.2832); ctx.stroke();
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(mpx.x - 5, mpx.y); ctx.lineTo(mpx.x + 5, mpx.y); ctx.moveTo(mpx.x, mpx.y - 5); ctx.lineTo(mpx.x, mpx.y + 5); ctx.stroke();
      // paths
      ["sgd", "mom", "adam"].forEach(function(key){
        var pth = paths[key]; if (!pth || pth.length === 0) return;
        ctx.strokeStyle = colors[key]; ctx.lineWidth = 2; ctx.beginPath();
        for (var i = 0; i < pth.length; i++){
          var pp = toPx(pth[i].x, pth[i].y);
          if (i === 0) ctx.moveTo(pp.x, pp.y); else ctx.lineTo(pp.x, pp.y);
        }
        ctx.stroke();
        var last = toPx(pth[pth.length - 1].x, pth[pth.length - 1].y);
        ctx.fillStyle = colors[key]; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(last.x, last.y, 4.5, 0, 6.2832); ctx.fill();
      });
      // start marker
      var sp = toPx(start.x, start.y);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "#e8e8ee"; ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(sp.x, sp.y, 5, 0, 6.2832); ctx.stroke();

      drawLoss();
      document.getElementById("optIt").textContent = iter;
      document.getElementById("optLs").textContent = hist.sgd.length ? fmt(hist.sgd[hist.sgd.length - 1], 4) : "--";
      document.getElementById("optLm").textContent = hist.mom.length ? fmt(hist.mom[hist.mom.length - 1], 4) : "--";
      document.getElementById("optLa").textContent = hist.adam.length ? fmt(hist.adam[hist.adam.length - 1], 4) : "--";
    }
    function drawLoss(){
      lctx.clearRect(0, 0, lc.width, lc.height); lctx.fillStyle = "#0a0a0c"; lctx.fillRect(0, 0, lc.width, lc.height);
      lctx.fillStyle = "#9aa0aa"; lctx.font = "10px ui-monospace"; lctx.fillText("loss vs iteration", 8, 14);
      var len = hist.sgd.length; if (len < 2) return;
      var mx = 0, keys = ["sgd", "mom", "adam"], ki, jj;
      for (ki = 0; ki < 3; ki++) for (jj = 0; jj < hist[keys[ki]].length; jj++) if (hist[keys[ki]][jj] > mx) mx = hist[keys[ki]][jj];
      if (mx <= 0) mx = 1;
      for (ki = 0; ki < 3; ki++){
        var h = hist[keys[ki]];
        lctx.strokeStyle = colors[keys[ki]]; lctx.lineWidth = 2; lctx.beginPath();
        for (jj = 0; jj < h.length; jj++){
          var x = 8 + jj / (h.length - 1) * (lc.width - 16);
          var y = lc.height - 12 - (h[jj] / mx) * (lc.height - 30);
          if (jj === 0) lctx.moveTo(x, y); else lctx.lineTo(x, y);
        }
        lctx.stroke();
      }
    }
    function loop(){ if (!running) return; for (var s = 0; s < 2; s++) step(); draw();
      if (iter > 600){ running = false; document.getElementById("optRun").textContent = "Run"; return; }
      raf = requestAnimationFrame(loop);
    }
    function lrFromSlider(){ lr = Math.pow(10, parseFloat(document.getElementById("optLr").value)); document.getElementById("optLrV").textContent = fmt(lr, lr < 0.01 ? 4 : 3); }

    cv.addEventListener("click", function(e){ var p = evtXY(cv, e); var m = toMath(p.x, p.y); start = { x: m.x, y: m.y }; running = false; document.getElementById("optRun").textContent = "Run"; reset(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("optSurf").addEventListener("change", function(){ surface = this.value; running = false; document.getElementById("optRun").textContent = "Run"; reset(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("optLr").addEventListener("input", lrFromSlider);
    document.getElementById("optRun").addEventListener("click", function(){ if (iter > 600) reset(); running = !running; this.textContent = running ? "Pause" : "Run"; if (running) loop(); });
    document.getElementById("optStep").addEventListener("click", function(){ for (var s = 0; s < 5; s++) step(); draw(); });
    document.getElementById("optReset").addEventListener("click", function(){ running = false; document.getElementById("optRun").textContent = "Run"; reset(); draw(); });

    lrFromSlider(); reset(); draw();
    return { draw: draw };
  })();

  // ---------- boot ----------
  switchExp("reg");

})();
</script>
</BaseLayout>
